WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:27.962 --> 00:29.530
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

00:33.134 --> 00:34.368
IGOR: <i>You know this story.</i>

00:39.540 --> 00:41.008
<i>The crack of lightning.</i>

00:45.880 --> 00:47.548
<i>A mad genius.</i>

00:52.553 --> 00:54.288
<i>An unholy creation.</i>

00:59.393 --> 01:01.462
<i>The world, of course,
remembers the monster,</i>

01:01.495 --> 01:02.897
<i>not the man.</i>

01:04.831 --> 01:07.034
<i>But sometimes,
when you look closely...</i>

01:07.068 --> 01:08.903
<i>there's more to a tale.</i>

01:10.438 --> 01:12.440
<i>Sometimes the monster
is the man.</i>

01:20.748 --> 01:23.084
<i>I've been with the circus
for as long as I can remember.</i>

01:24.452 --> 01:27.455
<i>Circuses like to think
of themselves as families.</i>

01:28.422 --> 01:31.525
<i>But, of course,
each one has its clown.</i>

01:32.526 --> 01:33.961
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)
(CIRCUS MUSIC PLAYING)

01:33.995 --> 01:35.162
(PANTING)

01:37.331 --> 01:38.566
Oh!

01:38.599 --> 01:39.599
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

01:42.870 --> 01:44.639
<i>I didn't have a name
back then.</i>

01:44.672 --> 01:46.907
<i>I was just "the hunchback".</i>

01:46.941 --> 01:48.943
<i>Or "freak",
if you were being kind.</i>

01:51.178 --> 01:53.714
<i>But the truth is,
I didn't hate them for it.</i>

01:53.748 --> 01:55.016
<i>It's hard to judge cruelty</i>

01:55.049 --> 01:56.617
<i>when you've
never known kindness.</i>

02:02.323 --> 02:05.493
<i>Besides, I always
had someone to look up to.</i>

02:31.385 --> 02:32.787
<i>When I wasn't performing,</i>

02:32.820 --> 02:35.289
<i>I served
as the company's doctor.</i>

02:35.323 --> 02:37.491
<i>I became fascinated by
the science of medicine.</i>

02:38.659 --> 02:39.859
<i>Particularly of human anatomy.</i>

02:43.064 --> 02:45.433
<i>I wanted to understand
everything about...</i>

02:45.466 --> 02:49.236
<i>...this internal universe
that makes us who we are.</i>

02:49.270 --> 02:53.274
<i>The brains, lungs,
bones, muscles.</i>

02:55.876 --> 02:57.144
<i>The heart.</i>

02:58.479 --> 03:00.181
<i>I don't know
why the science of life</i>

03:00.214 --> 03:02.283
<i>captured my imagination.</i>

03:03.317 --> 03:04.757
<i>I think
it just helped me escape.</i>

03:05.353 --> 03:06.554
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

03:06.587 --> 03:07.587
(IGOR MUTTERING)

03:08.356 --> 03:09.523
My God!

03:10.591 --> 03:13.894
You really think you're smart,
don't you, eh? Huh?

03:13.928 --> 03:15.996
A real intellectual.

03:16.030 --> 03:17.732
What an embarrassment
that must be!

03:18.399 --> 03:19.633
(MAN SHOUTING)

03:19.667 --> 03:20.768
Oi!

03:20.801 --> 03:22.069
You're on!

03:22.603 --> 03:23.604
(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING)

03:26.907 --> 03:28.175
IGOR: <i>Little did I know</i>

03:28.209 --> 03:30.044
<i>that on a chilly
London evening...</i>

03:30.077 --> 03:31.412
<i>...I was about to meet the man</i>

03:31.445 --> 03:34.382
<i>who would change
my life forever.</i>

03:34.415 --> 03:35.750
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

03:48.829 --> 03:50.197
(GROWLING)

04:02.309 --> 04:05.212
BARNABY: Ladies and gentlemen!

04:06.847 --> 04:09.417
Witness now
the death-defying feats

04:09.450 --> 04:11.952
of our very own
bird in the sky...

04:11.986 --> 04:15.823
The beautiful Lorelei!

04:16.589 --> 04:17.757
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

04:17.791 --> 04:18.791
(CIRCUS MUSIC PLAYING)

04:21.995 --> 04:23.396
(AUDIENCE GASPING
IN WONDERMENT)

04:47.021 --> 04:48.055
(ALL GASP)

04:48.089 --> 04:49.223
(GROANS)

04:49.490 --> 04:50.925
Lorelei!

04:50.958 --> 04:51.958
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

04:52.893 --> 04:54.128
Lorelei! Lorelei!

04:55.563 --> 04:56.664
Oh, Lorelei!

04:57.765 --> 04:59.600
She can't breathe!

04:59.633 --> 05:01.202
Previous injuries?

05:01.235 --> 05:02.736
Uh, she broke her arm
a year ago

05:02.770 --> 05:04.410
and her collarbone
sometime before that.

05:05.005 --> 05:07.408
Oh! Oh, my God.

05:08.209 --> 05:09.877
VICTOR: Collarbone
is rebroken,

05:09.910 --> 05:11.645
shoulder's dislocated,
causing pressure on the lungs.

05:11.679 --> 05:12.780
She can't breathe.

05:12.813 --> 05:13.814
(STAMMERING) What do we do?

05:13.848 --> 05:15.082
Nothing, I'm afraid.

05:15.116 --> 05:16.716
Don't have the tools
to reset the bone.

05:19.720 --> 05:21.889
Do you have a pocket watch?
Give it to me.

05:21.922 --> 05:23.802
I'm not giving you...
Do this now or she dies!

05:26.827 --> 05:28.162
Come on!

05:33.133 --> 05:34.133
VICTOR: Wait.

05:35.236 --> 05:37.071
That dislocation is
forcing the sternum

05:37.104 --> 05:38.472
to rest at an
untenable angle, yes?

05:38.506 --> 05:40.140
Yes. Ready?
Set?

05:40.174 --> 05:42.443
Three, two, one...

05:43.377 --> 05:44.845
(LORELEI GASPING)

05:46.347 --> 05:47.507
(EXCLAIMS) Yes!
There we are.

05:50.217 --> 05:52.253
LORELEI: You saved me.
Breathe.

05:52.286 --> 05:53.486
LORELEI: (PANTING) Thank you.

05:54.288 --> 05:55.489
VICTOR: That was incredible.

05:55.523 --> 05:57.491
Why are you wearing
that silly makeup?

05:57.525 --> 05:58.959
Well, I'm a clown.
You're not a clown,

05:58.993 --> 06:00.528
you're a physician...

06:00.561 --> 06:01.896
...who just performed
a dry surgery

06:01.929 --> 06:03.864
in less than a minute
with nothing to prepare.

06:03.898 --> 06:05.432
Well, I'm a clown physician.

06:05.466 --> 06:06.734
BARNABY: Don't panic,
ladies and gentlemen!

06:06.767 --> 06:08.335
All part of the act!

06:09.803 --> 06:10.905
You're being wasted here.

06:13.407 --> 06:14.975
I'm with the circus, sir.

06:15.009 --> 06:17.049
VICTOR: You're going to
leave the bloody circus.

06:17.144 --> 06:18.546
What's going on?

06:19.246 --> 06:20.581
You're a doctor, then?

06:20.614 --> 06:22.383
VICTOR: On my better days.

06:22.416 --> 06:24.084
Chiswick Cross Hospital
is just up the road.

06:24.118 --> 06:25.553
I can lead your men there now.

06:27.621 --> 06:28.889
Get her out of here sharpish!

06:28.923 --> 06:30.724
Go out the back way.
(LORELEI EXHALES DEEPLY)

06:30.758 --> 06:32.693
Don't want her
upsetting the clientele.

06:33.928 --> 06:35.863
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

06:35.896 --> 06:38.399
Where are they taking
that poor creature?

06:38.432 --> 06:40.834
Sir! Please,
may I know your name?

06:51.712 --> 06:53.948
(GASPS)
Ladies and gentlemen!

06:54.815 --> 06:56.717
The Human Cannonball!

06:56.750 --> 06:58.319
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

07:04.692 --> 07:06.260
Please, no!

07:06.293 --> 07:08.128
BARNABY: You sneaky rat!

07:08.162 --> 07:10.664
You want to leave? I own you!

07:10.698 --> 07:12.533
I've had enough
of these books!

07:12.566 --> 07:14.768
You belong to the circus!
Burn them!

07:14.802 --> 07:16.503
IGOR: Please, Master Barnaby,
it's my only thing.

07:16.537 --> 07:17.838
(STRONGMAN GRUNTING)

07:17.871 --> 07:20.074
No! No!
(BARNABY LAUGHS)

07:20.107 --> 07:21.542
Get out of there!
(GRUNTS)

07:22.543 --> 07:24.545
(BREATHING HEAVILY)
Let that be a lesson to you!

07:25.112 --> 07:26.413
Get in there!

07:26.447 --> 07:27.948
You are going nowhere!
(IGOR GROANS)

07:29.049 --> 07:30.451
(WOMEN LAUGHING)

07:31.785 --> 07:33.687
Do you know
what's happened to Lorelei?

07:39.927 --> 07:41.829
Romanticizing, are we?

07:44.365 --> 07:47.301
She's probably gonna die,
you know that.

07:48.636 --> 07:51.438
These city doctors
and their dirty hospitals.

07:53.374 --> 07:54.575
(LAUGHS)

07:54.608 --> 07:55.608
Ow!

08:23.437 --> 08:25.506
What are you doing?

08:25.539 --> 08:28.075
High powered magnet.
Should work. Usually does.

08:28.108 --> 08:29.943
Hold on, sir. You don't know
what he'll do to me.

08:29.977 --> 08:31.745
Don't I?
I can't just leave.

08:31.779 --> 08:33.614
Of course you can.
No, sir, they own me!

08:35.349 --> 08:37.717
You are better than this.
You can be better.

08:37.751 --> 08:40.287
I can get you out,
but you'll have to trust me, understand?

08:40.320 --> 08:42.655
BARNABY: Oi!

08:42.690 --> 08:44.810
Choose now or remain here
for the rest of your days.

08:45.826 --> 08:48.462
Get away from that cage!
You hear me?!

08:48.495 --> 08:49.563
Open it!
BARNABY: Oi!

08:51.899 --> 08:54.435
Get him!
He's property of the circus!

08:54.468 --> 08:55.736
Now, the thing is... (GRUNTS)

08:56.303 --> 08:57.805
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

08:59.173 --> 09:00.541
BARNABY: He's robbed us!

09:04.978 --> 09:07.981
The hunchback! He's attacked
me and robbed the circus!

09:08.415 --> 09:09.717
Get him!

09:12.419 --> 09:14.054
Get after him!

09:30.304 --> 09:31.572
(GRUNTS)
(GASPS)

09:33.173 --> 09:34.408
Don't touch him!

09:41.982 --> 09:42.982
Go!

09:44.051 --> 09:45.051
(BOTH GRUNTING)

09:54.394 --> 09:55.696
(FIREWORKS POPPING)

10:04.404 --> 10:05.439
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

10:06.573 --> 10:07.641
(LAUGHING)

10:13.413 --> 10:14.413
(CONTINUES LAUGHING)

10:16.016 --> 10:17.050
RAFFERTY: Got you.

10:17.885 --> 10:20.454
What do we do?
What do we do now?

10:26.727 --> 10:28.028
(GROANING)
MAN: Oh, shit.

10:30.998 --> 10:32.366
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

10:32.399 --> 10:34.067
(HORSES WHINNYING)

10:41.575 --> 10:43.544
How do we get out of here?

10:43.577 --> 10:45.479
You know this place, damn it!
How do we...

10:52.319 --> 10:53.487
BARNABY: Where are they?

10:53.520 --> 10:54.588
STRONGMAN: Whoa!

11:10.604 --> 11:12.239
(BOTH PANTING)

11:14.007 --> 11:15.175
(VICTOR LAUGHS)

11:17.477 --> 11:18.812
I'm not in the circus.

11:18.846 --> 11:19.847
What?

11:21.915 --> 11:23.116
Yes, very good.

11:23.550 --> 11:24.718
Come along!

11:26.186 --> 11:28.306
IGOR: I've never been
out of the circus before, sir.

11:37.130 --> 11:39.800
VICTOR: Eyes open, door shut.
Coat off.

11:51.511 --> 11:53.814
Coat off.

11:53.847 --> 11:56.950
We're going to slip into something
a little more comfortable.

11:59.419 --> 12:00.419
(DOOR OPENS)

12:01.521 --> 12:03.056
(INSTRUMENTS CLATTERING)

12:11.965 --> 12:12.965
(GRUNTS)

12:14.201 --> 12:15.201
What's that for?

12:17.337 --> 12:18.906
Next order of business.

12:20.340 --> 12:22.109
No. What are you
gonna do to me?

12:28.115 --> 12:29.716
Absolutely nothing.

12:30.417 --> 12:31.752
Don't worry about it.

12:34.988 --> 12:35.989
Look.

12:40.093 --> 12:41.562
This is going to hurt
just a little bit.

12:41.595 --> 12:42.930
(BOTH GRUNTING)

12:44.564 --> 12:46.733
What are you doing to me?
Listen to me!

12:47.167 --> 12:49.136
You are not...

12:49.636 --> 12:50.938
...a hunchback.

12:52.105 --> 12:53.140
(SCREAMING)

12:54.274 --> 12:56.843
Not a real one, anyway. No.

12:56.877 --> 12:58.679
You have an abscess...

12:58.712 --> 13:00.814
causing a fluid pocket,
a rather...

13:01.415 --> 13:03.884
...large fluid sac.

13:03.917 --> 13:05.452
It hurts!

13:05.485 --> 13:07.120
Yes, I imagine it does.

13:07.154 --> 13:08.834
You'd be surprised
how often I hear that.

13:10.958 --> 13:12.192
(GROANING)

13:15.662 --> 13:17.497
(VICTOR SPITS)

13:17.531 --> 13:18.999
Oh, looking at the size
of this beauty,

13:19.032 --> 13:20.672
I'd say it's gone
untreated for, oh...

13:20.701 --> 13:22.970
...18 years, but...

13:23.003 --> 13:24.304
...the good news is,
I'm convinced

13:24.338 --> 13:26.218
that if we can drain it...
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

13:27.407 --> 13:29.376
...in three...

13:30.277 --> 13:31.277
...two...

13:31.878 --> 13:33.680
...one. And pulling out.

13:33.714 --> 13:34.848
(IGOR GROANS)

13:35.549 --> 13:37.050
(IGOR PANTING)

13:38.852 --> 13:40.654
<i>Garde a l'eau!</i>
(PEOPLE SCREAM)

13:43.223 --> 13:44.223
(PANTING) Right.

13:44.791 --> 13:45.959
That's the easy part done.

13:45.993 --> 13:46.994
Easy part?

13:47.027 --> 13:48.027
(LAUGHS)

13:49.730 --> 13:51.098
(SCREAMS)
(BONES CRACKING)

13:51.832 --> 13:53.066
You're all right!

13:54.034 --> 13:56.737
And up... we... go.
(BOTH GRUNT)

13:57.871 --> 14:00.073
Now, your muscles...

14:00.774 --> 14:02.409
...your bones...

14:02.442 --> 14:05.045
...your entire
skeletal system...

14:05.078 --> 14:08.415
...will be struggling
to reset themselves...

14:08.448 --> 14:11.618
...to return you to
your former ground-sniffing...

14:11.651 --> 14:14.454
...Luddite-bearing posture
of the last...

14:14.488 --> 14:15.655
...18 years.

14:15.689 --> 14:17.891
So, for the time being,
my friend,

14:17.924 --> 14:19.793
you shall have to
wear this rather...

14:19.826 --> 14:22.095
...wonderful back brace
I constructed for Gordon.

14:22.429 --> 14:23.429
IGOR: Who?

14:25.832 --> 14:27.701
I'm standing up!

14:27.734 --> 14:29.136
That's rather obvious.

14:29.169 --> 14:31.171
I haven't overestimated
your intelligence, have I?

14:31.204 --> 14:32.506
It's just I'm not
in the circus

14:32.539 --> 14:33.539
and now I'm standing up.

14:34.241 --> 14:35.442
Yeah, you said that.

14:35.475 --> 14:37.077
Right!

14:37.110 --> 14:39.446
Library and study are over
there. Kitchen's over there.

14:39.479 --> 14:40.947
IGOR: I'm standing up.

14:40.981 --> 14:42.249
Your bedroom's on the right.

14:42.282 --> 14:44.551
There's a water heater
and soap in there.

14:44.584 --> 14:47.120
I suggest you use it
to do something about your...

14:47.754 --> 14:49.489
...hair.

14:49.523 --> 14:51.391
I'll be in the basement for
the rest of the evening,

14:51.425 --> 14:53.193
as I have school...

14:53.226 --> 14:54.528
...in the morning.
Make yourself at home,

14:54.561 --> 14:55.729
don't touch anything.

14:56.096 --> 14:57.664
Oh!

14:57.697 --> 15:00.534
By the way, I had,
have a flatmate.

15:00.567 --> 15:02.469
Goes by the name
of Igor Straussman.

15:02.502 --> 15:03.570
Man's a morphine addict.

15:03.603 --> 15:04.905
Idiot. Complete liar.

15:04.938 --> 15:06.273
Thankfully for us,
he's almost...

15:06.306 --> 15:07.974
...never home.

15:08.008 --> 15:10.544
So, should anyone question
your presence here,

15:10.577 --> 15:11.937
you are to say
that you are he.

15:12.512 --> 15:13.512
I'm Igor?

15:13.847 --> 15:14.915
Very good.

15:15.715 --> 15:16.883
(DOOR SLAMS)

15:19.886 --> 15:21.822
"Hello, my name is Igor."

15:27.994 --> 15:29.196
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

16:40.734 --> 16:41.968
TURPIN: Let's see.

16:42.002 --> 16:44.104
A dangerous hunchback is

16:44.137 --> 16:46.606
detained for the safety
of the public...

16:46.640 --> 16:49.109
...with a determined and
equally dangerous accomplice.

16:50.410 --> 16:53.246
They proceed
to the circus owner's trailer,

16:53.280 --> 16:55.782
where they rob the safe
of its contents.

16:55.815 --> 16:57.984
They make their violent
escape, culminating...

16:58.018 --> 16:59.452
...in the murder
of an innocent man,

16:59.486 --> 17:00.620
and vanishing...

17:02.656 --> 17:04.124
(ECHOING) ...into thin air.

17:07.127 --> 17:08.929
A fair summing up, Alistair?

17:08.962 --> 17:10.864
Yes, Inspector.

17:11.531 --> 17:13.599
Escape, robbery, murder.

17:14.733 --> 17:16.403
Just as Mr. Barnaby said.

17:22.275 --> 17:23.609
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

17:29.549 --> 17:31.549
TURPIN: Now here's what
I think happened, Alistair.

17:32.285 --> 17:34.888
A human being
with a spinal deformity

17:34.921 --> 17:37.123
is locked up against his will.

17:39.059 --> 17:41.261
Perhaps a common feature
of his treatment here.

17:42.796 --> 17:44.231
A stranger releases him...

17:45.031 --> 17:46.666
...using a magnet
and tickler...

17:47.901 --> 17:49.502
...as any fool can.

17:50.604 --> 17:54.074
They make their escape
urgently, as they must...

17:54.107 --> 17:55.675
...for the circus
is against them.

17:56.710 --> 17:58.011
They flee.

17:58.778 --> 18:00.247
A chase.

18:01.581 --> 18:03.016
A man dies.

18:05.719 --> 18:08.521
Manslaughter in self-defense
at most, I would say.

18:34.848 --> 18:36.850
"Wanted for murder."
Have it copied.

18:36.883 --> 18:37.784
I thought you said it wasn't...

18:37.817 --> 18:38.817
I did.

18:41.855 --> 18:44.224
Something tells me
our circus freak...

18:44.257 --> 18:46.426
may be only the beginning.

18:55.669 --> 18:56.736
Good morning!

19:06.212 --> 19:08.114
VICTOR: <i>Igor:
At school till six.</i>

19:08.148 --> 19:09.382
<i>Clothes in the wardrobe.</i>

19:09.416 --> 19:11.584
<i>Money and key
in the tin by the door.</i>

19:11.618 --> 19:13.353
<i>Be home for dinner. F.</i>

19:26.333 --> 19:28.234
IGOR: Chiswick Hospital.

19:57.664 --> 19:59.399
(INDISTINCT CLAMOR)

20:07.340 --> 20:09.509
(BARKERS SHOUTING
INDISTINCTLY)

20:53.119 --> 20:54.721
(DOCTOR SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

21:01.428 --> 21:02.896
Doctor?

21:02.929 --> 21:05.329
DOCTOR: This way, gentlemen.
We have amputation to perform.

21:07.500 --> 21:08.500
You.

21:09.335 --> 21:11.371
What, me?
Yeah.

21:11.404 --> 21:13.706
She needs camphor inhalations
twice a day,

21:13.740 --> 21:15.241
uh, extract of allium...

21:15.275 --> 21:17.243
...a quarter ounce of arsenic
and three of Filcher's Oil,

21:17.277 --> 21:18.411
but more if you can get it.

21:18.445 --> 21:20.613
I can't do that.
You can.

21:20.647 --> 21:23.616
(STAMMERING) And then
when she wakes, tell her...

21:24.250 --> 21:25.852
...a friend will be back.

21:59.152 --> 22:00.353
(DRIVER SHOUTING)

22:01.521 --> 22:02.521
(GROANS)

22:12.866 --> 22:14.167
TURPIN: Six months ago,

22:14.200 --> 22:16.369
a man tried to buy parts of
recently deceased animals...

22:16.402 --> 22:18.104
...at the London
Zoological Gardens.

22:18.138 --> 22:19.506
He was turned away.

22:19.539 --> 22:21.508
Two weeks later,
there was a forced entry.

22:21.541 --> 22:23.409
Animal limbs amputated
and stolen.

22:23.443 --> 22:25.144
A month later,
a similar pattern of events

22:25.178 --> 22:26.579
at the Veterinary Academy.

22:26.613 --> 22:28.581
ALISTAIR: Sounds gruesome,
but what...

22:28.615 --> 22:31.284
I confiscated that from
the crime scene at the circus.

22:31.784 --> 22:32.819
Open it.

22:39.959 --> 22:40.959
Sir...

22:43.897 --> 22:45.265
...this is disgusting.

22:46.733 --> 22:48.935
It belonged to a lioness
recently deceased.

22:51.371 --> 22:53.773
But it was found near our
murder victim at the circus...

22:53.806 --> 22:55.842
...and it didn't walk there
of its own accord.

22:57.510 --> 22:59.479
You think
there's a connection?

22:59.512 --> 23:01.180
I think our other man
at the circus

23:01.214 --> 23:02.694
fits the same description
as this...

23:03.016 --> 23:04.284
...animal thief.

23:06.452 --> 23:07.987
But who would do that?

23:09.055 --> 23:10.055
Huh?

23:12.058 --> 23:13.426
What motive?

23:14.928 --> 23:16.429
Something reeks here.

23:18.231 --> 23:20.433
It reeks of an evil,
sinful mischief.

23:20.466 --> 23:22.602
And now that man walks
the streets of this city.

23:39.419 --> 23:40.853
Back in the mud so soon?

23:45.858 --> 23:47.660
(CHUCKLES) Yes, I see.

23:47.694 --> 23:50.496
Absolutely savage depiction
of me, I'm afraid.

23:50.530 --> 23:52.332
(CLICKS TONGUE) Got the hair
all wrong, and the nose, too.

23:52.365 --> 23:54.133
I'm new to this criminal life,

23:54.167 --> 23:56.536
but I never thought the authorities
would attack my vanity.

23:56.569 --> 23:59.472
They think I'm a murderer!

23:59.505 --> 24:01.608
I've been called
much worse things in my time.

24:04.911 --> 24:07.647
Besides... they're not
looking for you...

24:08.081 --> 24:09.515
...are they?

24:09.549 --> 24:11.884
They're looking for a piteous,
nameless hunchback.

24:11.918 --> 24:15.054
And Igor, I would like you
to look at yourself.

24:16.689 --> 24:19.659
Igor, that creature
no longer exists.

24:22.762 --> 24:23.762
Dinner.

24:34.140 --> 24:35.775
This is excellent.

24:37.577 --> 24:41.080
So... what brought you to
the circus in the first place?

24:41.814 --> 24:42.814
Cutlery.

24:44.117 --> 24:45.518
What?
Use it.

24:45.918 --> 24:46.918
Oh. Sorry.

24:47.220 --> 24:48.521
Wipe your hands.

24:51.057 --> 24:52.057
Animals.

24:53.626 --> 24:54.661
Parts.

24:56.696 --> 24:59.632
I am a student at
the Royal College of Medicine.

24:59.666 --> 25:01.267
The curriculum
is straightforward,

25:01.300 --> 25:03.503
the exams easy,
the professors...

25:03.536 --> 25:06.539
Oh! The professors are
men of limited ability

25:06.572 --> 25:08.174
and even more limited horizon.

25:08.207 --> 25:10.410
Why did you rescue me?

25:11.477 --> 25:13.913
You, my friend,
were an unexpected gift.

25:13.946 --> 25:15.948
It's not every day
I come across a man,

25:15.982 --> 25:18.685
albeit one suffering from
such grotesque deformity...

25:18.718 --> 25:23.222
...who is so clearly talented,
observant, and resourceful...

25:23.256 --> 25:27.694
...and in possession of the most
gifted pair of hands I have ever seen.

25:28.795 --> 25:30.830
My interest in you
does not stem from charity.

25:31.130 --> 25:32.999
Follow me.

25:33.032 --> 25:35.468
Before I met you,
I was to approach Mr. Barnaby

25:35.501 --> 25:37.770
about acquiring some of
your deceased animals.

25:37.804 --> 25:39.605
To what end? Study?

25:40.139 --> 25:41.641
(LAUGHING)

25:41.674 --> 25:44.677
No, not as you would
think of it.

25:44.711 --> 25:46.312
I am of the strong belief
that death

25:46.345 --> 25:48.481
can be made
a temporary condition.

25:48.514 --> 25:49.982
That's impossible.
Improbable, yes.

25:50.016 --> 25:51.016
Impossible, no.

25:51.451 --> 25:52.752
Life is temporary.

25:52.785 --> 25:54.921
Why should death
be any different?

25:54.954 --> 25:57.123
(LAUGHS) I have absolutely
no time for false modesty.

25:57.156 --> 25:58.758
So it is without pride
or shame

25:58.791 --> 26:00.351
that I declare my discovery
an act of...

26:00.793 --> 26:01.894
...genius.

26:07.900 --> 26:09.402
Those eyes...

26:09.435 --> 26:13.473
...they're over
three months old.

26:13.506 --> 26:15.942
And the liquid is an
electrically conductive jelly

26:15.975 --> 26:17.643
of my own device.

26:17.677 --> 26:20.046
Serves a double function:
To preserve and to...

26:21.047 --> 26:23.049
Well, just wait and see.

26:23.983 --> 26:26.886
It's all a matter
of conversion, you see?

26:26.919 --> 26:30.056
The conversion
of pure electrical energy

26:30.089 --> 26:31.824
into the biological variety...

26:31.858 --> 26:34.260
...that flows
through the human body.

26:34.293 --> 26:35.813
Hence, the construction
of this device:

26:36.229 --> 26:38.164
The Lazarus Fork.

26:38.197 --> 26:41.868
I have found that by passing
that current through a...

26:41.901 --> 26:44.804
...specially blended variety
of sulfates and metals...

26:44.837 --> 26:46.539
You've mastered
the conversion?

26:47.073 --> 26:48.073
Yes.

26:48.941 --> 26:50.042
Well, show me.

27:07.126 --> 27:08.126
Ready?

27:16.903 --> 27:18.938
There. Do you see?

27:20.339 --> 27:21.674
They live.

27:23.042 --> 27:24.042
(VICTOR LAUGHING)

27:26.312 --> 27:27.713
What do you think?

27:29.315 --> 27:31.050
It is impressive.

27:31.083 --> 27:33.085
But you have
made a mess of the nerves.

27:34.053 --> 27:35.087
(STAMMERING)

27:35.922 --> 27:37.457
I beg your pardon?

27:37.490 --> 27:38.891
The oculomotor nerves.

27:38.925 --> 27:40.793
You haven't
connected them properly.

27:40.827 --> 27:42.829
That's why
they don't move evenly.

27:44.463 --> 27:45.698
You.

27:47.633 --> 27:48.835
(VICTOR LAUGHING)

27:59.445 --> 28:01.013
There he is!

28:01.447 --> 28:03.216
That's the man.

28:03.249 --> 28:04.483
That's the man I'm after.

28:04.517 --> 28:05.685
Thank you for asking.

28:06.319 --> 28:07.787
You're welcome.

28:07.820 --> 28:10.556
Now, I shall bring you
your assignments piecemeal.

28:10.590 --> 28:12.058
You will complete them
in a timely fashion,

28:12.091 --> 28:15.328
whereon I shall apply them
to a larger...

28:15.361 --> 28:17.530
...whole of my own device.
Questions?

28:17.563 --> 28:19.398
Uh, this larger whole...

28:19.432 --> 28:21.567
...is not of your concern.

28:21.601 --> 28:22.568
(STAMMERING) Well, but if I...

28:22.602 --> 28:23.736
Igor, I...

28:30.676 --> 28:32.979
All this is now yours.

28:33.012 --> 28:35.381
Every book. Every piece
of reference material.

28:35.414 --> 28:36.414
Apparatus. Desk.

28:37.416 --> 28:39.318
Room. Your laboratory,
if you like.

28:45.791 --> 28:48.861
As my assistant, you shall be
at the very heart...

28:48.895 --> 28:52.198
...of a scientific enterprise
that will change the world.

28:54.700 --> 28:56.335
Now, will you help me?

29:12.585 --> 29:14.220
Yeah. Fix that.

29:14.253 --> 29:15.688
Ah. Thank you.

29:20.293 --> 29:21.327
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)

29:28.801 --> 29:30.102
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)
Mmm-hmm.

29:33.573 --> 29:34.573
(VICTOR GRUNTING)

29:40.413 --> 29:41.847
VICTOR: Keep working on it.

29:50.189 --> 29:51.257
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

29:52.458 --> 29:53.538
(FAINT RHYTHMIC THUMPING)

30:44.610 --> 30:46.730
IGOR: <i>The hospital made
arrangements for Lorelei.</i>

30:47.380 --> 30:49.048
<i>She now had a benefactor.</i>

30:50.650 --> 30:52.118
<i>I was pleased
she had recovered</i>

30:52.151 --> 30:54.520
<i>and had someone
to look after her, but...</i>

30:54.553 --> 30:57.423
<i>...as the weeks went by,
I missed her.</i>

30:57.456 --> 31:00.059
<i>And I wondered if her life
had changed as much as mine.</i>

31:00.726 --> 31:02.695
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

31:02.728 --> 31:04.463
(FAINT RHYTHMIC THUMPING)

31:21.080 --> 31:22.080
(DOOR OPENING)

31:22.948 --> 31:23.949
Uh...

31:24.583 --> 31:25.918
Victor?
Mmm-hmm?

31:25.951 --> 31:27.853
This letter
for Master Straussman.

31:27.887 --> 31:30.356
We are going out on the town.
Oh!

31:32.358 --> 31:33.959
VICTOR: Here we are.

31:33.993 --> 31:35.661
I have a tenured membership
at the club,

31:35.694 --> 31:37.696
thanks to my father's...
(CLEARS THROAT)

31:37.730 --> 31:39.298
...status as a charter member.

31:39.331 --> 31:40.733
Bought the velvet
for the seats.

31:40.766 --> 31:42.001
IGOR: Your father...

31:42.034 --> 31:43.769
VICTOR: Is what they call
a great man.

31:43.803 --> 31:46.672
Esteemed doctor,

31:46.705 --> 31:49.041
member of the Royal College
of Physicians, and...

31:49.075 --> 31:51.177
...pioneer in the field
of cardio-physiology.

31:51.210 --> 31:52.611
I should be honored
to meet him someday.

31:52.645 --> 31:54.847
Uh, perhaps not.
Look, here's the club!

31:54.880 --> 31:56.015
Master Victor, I'm not sure
I'm suited for this.

31:56.048 --> 31:57.383
Pish!

31:57.416 --> 31:59.218
Just keep your back straight,
your words clean,

31:59.251 --> 32:01.687
and do your damnedest
not to embarrass me.

32:01.720 --> 32:04.156
Babies grown in vats!

32:04.190 --> 32:06.158
Victor, do you think this is

32:06.192 --> 32:07.927
really the appropriate place
to talk about this?

32:07.960 --> 32:09.662
Help me!
I am just trying to inform

32:09.695 --> 32:12.364
these two wonderful
young ladies that...

32:12.398 --> 32:15.067
...fertilization needn't take
place inside the female body.

32:15.534 --> 32:17.236
Sperm! Sperms!

32:17.269 --> 32:18.971
Can sperm move?

32:19.004 --> 32:20.673
They can.
Thank you.

32:20.706 --> 32:22.608
Why can't
it move independently

32:22.641 --> 32:24.510
towards the egg in, say, a...

32:24.543 --> 32:26.145
(STAMMERING)

32:27.246 --> 32:28.781
...bucket?

32:28.814 --> 32:30.349
Where does the mother fit in?

32:31.617 --> 32:34.286
Exactly!
You're off educating yourself!

32:34.320 --> 32:36.989
By the time we need you,
we're...

32:37.022 --> 32:40.059
...sucking the fertilized egg
up into a funnel

32:40.092 --> 32:41.452
and then we shuck it
up your...

32:41.994 --> 32:43.896
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

32:49.502 --> 32:51.036
(INAUDIBLE)

32:52.638 --> 32:54.039
Igor?

32:54.073 --> 32:56.008
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

33:36.649 --> 33:37.917
LORELEI: Excuse me?

33:40.953 --> 33:42.454
Sorry, I thought
I recognized you.

33:42.488 --> 33:43.488
Well, you might do.

33:44.757 --> 33:46.358
I don't remember your name.

33:46.392 --> 33:48.561
Well, I never had one.

33:54.767 --> 33:55.935
(GASPS)

33:57.469 --> 33:58.504
It's you.

33:58.537 --> 33:59.537
It's me.

34:01.040 --> 34:02.608
Well, yeah, a bit different.

34:06.078 --> 34:07.613
You saved my life.

34:09.849 --> 34:11.317
My life.

34:12.952 --> 34:14.353
(MAN LAUGHING)

34:16.688 --> 34:19.058
Boring!

34:19.091 --> 34:20.592
IGOR: Friend of yours?

34:22.695 --> 34:23.996
That's Baron Bomine.

34:24.029 --> 34:26.599
He recruited me
to be in his cabaret...

34:26.632 --> 34:28.634
...and his consort in public.

34:29.969 --> 34:31.270
Right.
(BOMINE LAUGHING)

34:32.404 --> 34:35.341
He, uh... prefers
the company of men.

34:35.808 --> 34:36.942
Oh.

34:39.945 --> 34:42.348
(STAMMERS) I have a name now.

34:42.748 --> 34:44.216
I am Igor.

34:44.917 --> 34:45.951
(LAUGHS)

34:46.784 --> 34:47.784
What?

34:51.924 --> 34:53.458
It's perfect.

34:53.492 --> 34:55.094
VICTOR: This woman
seems to think

34:55.127 --> 34:56.895
that the human brain is pink.

34:56.929 --> 34:58.449
(PEOPLE GASPING)
In fact, it is grey.

34:58.764 --> 35:00.566
That's Victor Frankenstein.

35:00.599 --> 35:02.468
Grey like this oyster.
I'm done. (TRAY CLATTERS)

35:02.501 --> 35:04.737
He's the man who rescued me.
And he helped save you.

35:04.770 --> 35:06.438
Is he always like that?

35:06.472 --> 35:09.875
No. He's very clever,
and he is kind.

35:09.909 --> 35:11.944
He just finds
ordinary people very...

35:11.977 --> 35:13.379
...ordinary.

35:13.913 --> 35:15.047
Victor, how did you...

35:15.080 --> 35:16.148
Who are you?

35:17.049 --> 35:20.719
You're the fallen angel.

35:20.753 --> 35:23.522
Plummeted from any other great
heights lately? (LAUGHING)

35:25.391 --> 35:27.860
Maybe you should try this one.
It's only, oh...

35:27.893 --> 35:29.962
...all of 30 feet.
You've had worse.

35:29.995 --> 35:31.597
I'm afraid the only thing
plummeting here

35:31.630 --> 35:33.766
is my opinion of you,
Mr. Frankenschteen.

35:33.799 --> 35:35.768
Frankenstein.
All right, Victor.

35:35.801 --> 35:38.037
Igor, um... (LAUGHS)

35:38.070 --> 35:39.938
Igor speaks
very highly of you.

35:39.972 --> 35:41.740
Would you like to join us?

35:41.774 --> 35:43.242
(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING)

35:43.275 --> 35:44.944
Now, of course,
I can't tell you everything,

35:44.977 --> 35:46.378
but suffice it to say...

35:46.412 --> 35:49.581
...Igor and I stand upon
the cusp of...

35:49.615 --> 35:53.485
...creating life out of death.

35:53.519 --> 35:54.920
(VICTOR LAUGHS)

35:54.953 --> 35:57.056
Mr. Frankenstein...
Victor. Please.

35:57.089 --> 36:00.392
I find your promise
more than a little unsettling.

36:00.426 --> 36:01.927
Ooh.

36:01.960 --> 36:04.263
Superstitious, are we?
No.

36:04.296 --> 36:06.932
Are you not afraid to
challenge the natural order?

36:06.965 --> 36:08.600
Igor, speak up.
What do you think?

36:10.703 --> 36:12.638
Once, I would have agreed
with you, Lorelei,

36:12.671 --> 36:13.939
but think about it.

36:13.973 --> 36:15.341
Twenty years ago,
electric lights

36:15.374 --> 36:17.276
would have been
thought of as magic.

36:17.309 --> 36:20.245
Your injuries in the circus
would have been fatal.

36:20.279 --> 36:22.314
Every day science
and technology

36:22.348 --> 36:23.916
changes the way
we live our lives.

36:23.949 --> 36:25.284
Look at me.

36:25.317 --> 36:27.052
Well said, that man.

36:27.086 --> 36:28.087
Life and death are different.

36:28.120 --> 36:29.488
"Life and death!"

36:29.521 --> 36:32.758
I dream of a world
where hope replaces fear.

36:32.791 --> 36:34.660
A world where a murdered man

36:34.693 --> 36:36.428
can stand in court
to face his murderer.

36:36.462 --> 36:38.931
Where a crippled soldier,
shrapnel in his spine...

36:38.964 --> 36:40.933
...can be killed, healed,

36:40.966 --> 36:42.606
then brought back to life
to walk again.

36:43.902 --> 36:45.771
Don't you see?
The possibilities are...

36:46.939 --> 36:50.009
...endless! Life is beautiful!

36:50.042 --> 36:52.678
But unfortunately
it is finite.

36:52.711 --> 36:53.911
Now, tell me what that says.

36:54.913 --> 36:57.316
"Death."
Thank you very much.

36:57.349 --> 37:00.319
I cannot argue with that.

37:00.352 --> 37:03.122
There it is,
in black and white.

37:03.155 --> 37:05.557
But with a little
applied science...

37:08.260 --> 37:10.562
...what do I give you now?

37:10.596 --> 37:12.398
(CHUCKLES) "Life."

37:13.232 --> 37:14.752
VICTOR: That's
what I'm trying to do.

37:15.801 --> 37:17.803
Perhaps I spoke too soon.

37:21.573 --> 37:23.333
VICTOR: <i>You shouldn't
see that girl again.</i>

37:23.409 --> 37:24.309
What? Why?

37:24.343 --> 37:25.778
Well, she's very nice.

37:25.811 --> 37:28.147
Uneducated, superstitious.
Distraction from our work.

37:28.180 --> 37:29.481
She's kind to me.

37:29.515 --> 37:31.350
Tonight was not about
meaningless frivolity.

37:31.383 --> 37:34.286
It was a celebration
of our work together.

37:34.319 --> 37:37.856
I think it is high time...
you met our monster.

37:44.897 --> 37:46.865
Don't tarry! Come, come, come!

37:49.001 --> 37:50.169
Come on!

37:56.942 --> 37:58.310
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

38:33.011 --> 38:34.546
What is that?
Gordon.

38:35.981 --> 38:37.649
What?
Gordon! (GRUNTING)

38:40.185 --> 38:41.720
(STAMMERS) You made this?

38:41.753 --> 38:42.753
VICTOR: No, no, no.

38:43.689 --> 38:46.225
We... made this.

38:47.926 --> 38:50.696
Lungs, heart, spine, brain...

38:50.729 --> 38:51.897
...all your work.

38:54.600 --> 38:56.335
All...

38:56.368 --> 38:58.537
...impossible without you,
in fact.

39:00.506 --> 39:01.640
Victor...

39:05.377 --> 39:08.514
You promised me
this was all about life.

39:09.448 --> 39:11.250
It's about more than that.

39:18.724 --> 39:19.724
Hands off.

39:21.894 --> 39:23.328
Three... two...

39:24.096 --> 39:25.197
...one.

39:33.238 --> 39:34.758
(WHISPERING)
Come on, come on, come on.

39:34.840 --> 39:36.275
Shh!

39:38.544 --> 39:39.578
Look.

39:49.688 --> 39:50.722
(LAUGHING SOFTLY)

39:52.624 --> 39:53.992
It's alive.

39:54.026 --> 39:57.596
Yes, it's... alive.

39:57.629 --> 39:58.864
It's alive?

39:59.932 --> 40:02.334
Victor... how?

40:02.367 --> 40:04.536
Can't quite move yet.

40:04.570 --> 40:06.338
Charge lasts barely an hour,

40:06.371 --> 40:07.839
and the bottom half

40:07.873 --> 40:09.608
is predominantly
a rude mockup.

40:09.641 --> 40:12.311
You have created life
out of nothing!

40:12.344 --> 40:14.446
Do you realize
how significant this is?

40:14.479 --> 40:15.981
Oh, I have an inkling.

40:17.416 --> 40:19.918
You are to accompany me
to the college tomorrow.

40:19.952 --> 40:21.954
I've announced that
I'll be making a presentation

40:21.987 --> 40:24.022
of my private work.

40:24.056 --> 40:25.791
I'm coming to the college
with you?

40:25.824 --> 40:27.025
As your assistant?

40:28.493 --> 40:30.729
Igor, try not to be
quite so dim.

40:31.496 --> 40:33.599
From this day forth...

40:33.632 --> 40:37.369
...you are to be my partner.

40:39.972 --> 40:40.972
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

40:48.280 --> 40:49.881
MAID: Letter for you,
Miss Lorelei.

40:51.149 --> 40:53.018
Letter? From who?

41:01.893 --> 41:03.895
IGOR: <i>Dear Lorelei:
We've had a breakthrough.</i>

41:03.929 --> 41:05.964
<i>Please come to
the Royal College of Medicine,</i>

41:05.998 --> 41:07.799
<i>Hall H, this evening at 8 PM.</i>

41:08.166 --> 41:09.166
<i>Igor.</i>

41:10.469 --> 41:12.371
Big presentation in Hall H.

41:13.538 --> 41:15.307
Presentation in Hall H.

41:16.275 --> 41:20.512
Big presentation, Hall H!

41:20.545 --> 41:21.980
Igor, around to the right.

41:29.554 --> 41:32.791
Since the beginning
of modern medicine...

41:32.824 --> 41:35.627
...there has been
an assumption...

41:35.661 --> 41:39.665
...regarding the status
of mortality...

41:39.698 --> 41:41.800
...that being that death...

41:41.833 --> 41:43.468
...is an unavoidable...

41:44.503 --> 41:48.540
...event, the inevitability of
which we should...

41:48.573 --> 41:50.542
...take for granted.

41:50.575 --> 41:52.077
(STAMMERS) I will show...

41:53.612 --> 41:56.882
(CLEARS THROAT) ...today
that life is not some...

41:58.383 --> 42:01.820
...grace bestowed
upon us by...

42:01.853 --> 42:03.755
...some outdated notion of
an all-powerful...

42:03.789 --> 42:06.992
Get on with it.

42:07.025 --> 42:10.095
Yes, of course. I'm not
accustomed to public speaking.

42:10.128 --> 42:12.698
Igor, would you prime
the dynamo for me, please?

42:12.731 --> 42:13.832
Yes, master.

42:15.133 --> 42:19.337
I would like to show you,
uh, show all seven of you...

42:19.371 --> 42:21.173
...and, of course,
the young lady...

42:21.206 --> 42:22.841
Come on, come on!

42:22.874 --> 42:23.909
I have a coach waiting.

42:25.410 --> 42:26.745
Uh... (SIGHS)

42:26.778 --> 42:28.113
(STAMMERS)

42:28.146 --> 42:30.716
I give to you... life...

42:31.550 --> 42:34.386
...by my own... creation.

42:43.095 --> 42:44.463
MAN: (SCOFFS) Cattle market.

42:47.699 --> 42:52.037
I have built this homunculus
from various body parts...

42:52.070 --> 42:54.673
...I got from...
the London Zoo.

42:54.706 --> 42:56.141
They've had a terrible time
with the upkeep

42:56.174 --> 42:57.476
of their exotic animals,

42:57.509 --> 42:58.744
all to my benefit.

42:58.777 --> 43:00.712
He's mainly chimpanzee...

43:00.746 --> 43:02.314
...but with the aid of
my esteemed associate,

43:02.347 --> 43:03.582
Igor Straussman,

43:03.615 --> 43:05.016
we've managed to interlace...

43:05.050 --> 43:06.585
...multiple individuals,

43:06.618 --> 43:09.688
multiple species
as a matter of fact.

43:09.721 --> 43:11.823
Igor, is it ready?
They're staring at me.

43:11.857 --> 43:13.258
Thank you.

43:13.291 --> 43:15.160
Do come to the front.
Get a closer look.

43:15.193 --> 43:16.193
Don't be shy.

43:18.263 --> 43:20.165
He won't bite.

43:20.198 --> 43:23.835
Now, by the miracle
of electricity...

43:24.603 --> 43:28.774
...I give you in three,
two, one...

43:29.708 --> 43:31.109
...life.

43:31.143 --> 43:32.863
(FLIES BUZZING)
(MEN EXCLAIMING IN DISGUST)

43:33.812 --> 43:34.813
(MAN LAUGHING)

43:37.015 --> 43:38.316
God!

43:38.350 --> 43:40.185
MAN: I've seen enough.

43:40.218 --> 43:41.453
(LAUGHS MOCKINGLY)
No!

43:42.154 --> 43:43.722
Don't go!

43:43.755 --> 43:45.924
Igor, shock him again. Harder.

43:48.093 --> 43:50.328
Three, two, one... now!

43:50.362 --> 43:51.563
(SHOUTS)

43:52.397 --> 43:53.765
(FINNEGAN LAUGHS)

43:53.799 --> 43:56.201
Frankenstein, you've surpassed...
(SCREAMS IN PAIN)

43:56.234 --> 43:58.303
...all expectations, even by

43:58.336 --> 44:01.440
your own expansive mythos of
strangeness and perversion.

44:01.473 --> 44:03.475
This is spectacular.
It's delightful!

44:04.142 --> 44:06.311
Just an exquisite show of...

44:06.344 --> 44:07.612
...depraved lunacy.

44:07.913 --> 44:08.914
Igor.

44:09.581 --> 44:11.016
Full charge.

44:11.383 --> 44:12.751
Ready?

44:16.221 --> 44:17.989
Igor?
Ready.

44:18.456 --> 44:19.558
Now!

44:20.392 --> 44:21.593
(SCREAMING)

44:22.861 --> 44:24.663
(BOTH GROAN)

44:24.696 --> 44:26.998
FINNEGAN: Oh, look,
there she goes, Victor.

44:27.032 --> 44:29.167
Bing, bang... boom.

44:30.402 --> 44:31.770
What have you got next?

44:33.004 --> 44:34.706
Perhaps a midget

44:34.739 --> 44:36.808
hidden inside your rotting
meat sculpture's stomach...

44:36.842 --> 44:38.910
...ready to pop out
with a bouquet of ro...

44:40.045 --> 44:41.045
(FAINT WHEEZING)

44:48.286 --> 44:49.521
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

45:03.268 --> 45:04.536
Do you see?

45:20.585 --> 45:21.853
(GROANS)
(LORELEI SHOUTS)

45:24.256 --> 45:25.957
(GASPS)
(GROWLING)

45:35.233 --> 45:36.233
It's all right.

45:37.035 --> 45:38.570
Gordon... Gordon...

45:39.404 --> 45:41.172
Igor!
Lorelei, stay back!

45:53.351 --> 45:54.351
(SCREECHING)

45:59.291 --> 46:01.293
Lorelei, are you all right?
Igor!

46:01.326 --> 46:02.661
I'm fine.

46:02.694 --> 46:04.596
VICTOR: Don't let him escape.

46:05.196 --> 46:06.196
(IGOR PANTING)

46:30.822 --> 46:31.823
(FLY BUZZING)
(GASPS)

46:55.447 --> 46:56.447
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)

47:19.704 --> 47:20.739
(IGOR GRUNTING)

47:23.041 --> 47:24.275
Gordon! Stop!

47:25.377 --> 47:26.544
Ahh!

47:26.578 --> 47:27.712
(PANTING)

47:37.956 --> 47:39.424
(MEN CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)

47:39.457 --> 47:41.459
No, no! Don't go out there!

47:51.169 --> 47:52.169
(SNARLING)

48:04.783 --> 48:06.051
(IGOR GRUNTING)

48:09.154 --> 48:10.655
Victor!

48:10.688 --> 48:12.390
Calm down, Gordon.
Get him off me!

48:12.424 --> 48:13.658
Gordon?

48:13.692 --> 48:14.826
Victor!

48:14.859 --> 48:15.927
(GRUNTING)

48:16.694 --> 48:17.796
Ahh!

48:19.130 --> 48:21.332
Igor,
what have you done to him?

48:21.366 --> 48:22.446
Victor! Help me, not him!

48:28.540 --> 48:29.974
Victor, we have to kill it!

48:33.478 --> 48:34.478
(PANTING)

48:35.647 --> 48:37.182
Do it, Victor!

48:38.216 --> 48:39.216
(GRUNTING)

48:41.553 --> 48:42.854
IGOR: <i>It was out of control!</i>

48:42.887 --> 48:44.923
We made progress today!

48:44.956 --> 48:46.958
It was homicidal!

48:46.991 --> 48:49.060
I had no way of knowing
that Gordon...

48:49.094 --> 48:50.774
Am I to understand
that you built that?

48:51.062 --> 48:52.363
Yes!

48:58.136 --> 48:59.237
I apologize.

49:00.338 --> 49:02.841
I misjudged you.

49:03.541 --> 49:04.843
Your flaws, though they're...

49:05.844 --> 49:08.179
...glaring and massive,
are merely social...

49:08.746 --> 49:09.981
...not intellectual.

49:11.649 --> 49:13.118
I find your work
astonishing...

49:14.252 --> 49:15.987
...and to be
perfectly frank...

49:16.888 --> 49:19.824
...brilliant. Brilliant!

49:19.858 --> 49:22.861
Quite beyond
my own ability to comprehend.

49:25.697 --> 49:26.931
Could you create another one?

49:26.965 --> 49:29.968
I could,
and a whole lot more beside.

49:31.703 --> 49:34.973
But that would take
considerable resource.

49:35.006 --> 49:36.474
As you are aware,

49:36.508 --> 49:38.676
I do come from the third
richest family in England.

49:38.710 --> 49:40.678
As a result, I can provide you

49:40.712 --> 49:42.152
with whatever it is
you so require.

49:42.614 --> 49:44.916
In that case, yes.

49:44.949 --> 49:47.418
And when you say... "more"?

49:47.819 --> 49:49.020
A man.

49:51.089 --> 49:53.758
A thinking, intelligent being.

49:53.791 --> 49:54.893
Can we discuss this?

49:54.926 --> 49:56.294
FINNEGAN:
I like this ambition.

49:56.327 --> 49:58.930
You were right, Igor.
The beast was dangerous...

49:58.963 --> 50:00.532
...but now we have
the opportunity

50:00.565 --> 50:02.300
to show the value of our work.

50:02.333 --> 50:06.304
You and I, Igor... we shall
create a man after our own...

50:06.738 --> 50:08.039
...image.

50:09.474 --> 50:10.909
Think of it.

50:12.677 --> 50:13.677
An intelligent...

50:14.379 --> 50:16.047
...civilized...

50:17.448 --> 50:18.917
...man.

50:22.687 --> 50:24.322
I'll want
another demonstration.

50:25.456 --> 50:27.525
I want to know whether you can
take direction.

50:27.559 --> 50:28.760
Follow orders, so to speak.

50:28.793 --> 50:30.495
Is that a problem?

50:30.528 --> 50:32.564
Victor, we cannot.
No.

50:32.597 --> 50:33.898
Excellent!

50:36.000 --> 50:37.569
Expect to hear from me soon.

50:41.773 --> 50:44.175
You did not create
this technology

50:44.209 --> 50:45.710
and yet you presume to
tell me how to use it.

50:45.743 --> 50:47.212
You should know your place!

50:50.081 --> 50:52.550
Your ignorance
of the ways of the world

50:52.584 --> 50:54.552
cannot hinder the furtherment
of my experimentation.

50:54.586 --> 50:56.621
But surely you see
you have no control.

50:56.654 --> 50:58.590
Surely you have forgotten

50:58.623 --> 51:00.358
what I did for you
at the circus!

51:02.427 --> 51:06.297
This is my destiny.
It is your destiny.

51:06.331 --> 51:10.568
And that man represents
our only ally on this planet.

51:10.602 --> 51:13.705
And if he wants us to make him
an entire zoo of homunculi,

51:13.738 --> 51:15.573
that is exactly
what we will do...

51:15.607 --> 51:17.976
...if it ensures the
furtherment of our research.

51:18.009 --> 51:20.111
Am I making myself clear?

51:20.712 --> 51:22.380
Am I making myself clear?!

51:22.413 --> 51:23.514
Yes, Victor!

51:47.171 --> 51:48.406
(THUNDER CRASHING)

51:56.080 --> 51:57.282
(FLIES BUZZING)

52:04.889 --> 52:06.424
BARNABY: <i>I own you!</i>

52:07.759 --> 52:08.839
<i>You belong to the circus!</i>

52:09.594 --> 52:10.762
(MOCKING LAUGHTER)

52:10.795 --> 52:12.030
(GASPS)

52:14.933 --> 52:16.434
(BANGING ON DOOR)

52:19.604 --> 52:22.073
Good morning. Can I help you?

52:22.106 --> 52:24.575
Detective Inspector Turpin,
Scotland Yard.

52:26.511 --> 52:28.579
I want to speak with
a Mr. Frankenstein.

52:30.081 --> 52:31.649
I'm afraid
that's not convenient

52:31.683 --> 52:32.951
at the moment, sir.

52:32.984 --> 52:34.986
May I know your business?

52:58.076 --> 52:59.544
Do you miss the circus?

53:01.879 --> 53:03.414
I'm not sure
what you mean, sir.

53:04.582 --> 53:06.084
Get me Frankenstein.

53:28.206 --> 53:30.708
I've informed the college
I would happily pay

53:30.742 --> 53:32.310
for the damage.
Just a bit of broken glass.

53:32.343 --> 53:34.078
An animal
was involved apparently.

53:34.112 --> 53:35.913
There was indeed.

53:35.947 --> 53:38.783
Mr. Straussman and I are currently
involved in the study of...

53:39.417 --> 53:41.185
...chimpanzees.

53:41.219 --> 53:45.223
It's quite... quite
fascinating, actually.

53:45.256 --> 53:47.792
We have discovered that
by using emotional cues...

53:47.825 --> 53:50.495
...we can teach them
primitive belief systems.

53:50.528 --> 53:52.163
Of course, it's only because
they are not yet capable

53:52.196 --> 53:54.399
of higher logical thought.

53:55.666 --> 53:56.601
Where is the creature now?

53:56.634 --> 53:58.169
Dead.

53:58.202 --> 54:00.505
Poor thing.
Had to be put down, didn't it?

54:00.538 --> 54:03.040
Why would the police be
interested in such a trifle?

54:03.074 --> 54:04.409
There may be a connection

54:04.442 --> 54:05.922
with a murder investigation
of ours.

54:06.778 --> 54:08.212
Murder investigation?

54:08.246 --> 54:10.181
Igor, this is
a murder investigation!

54:10.214 --> 54:11.482
Am I to understand
we have to summon

54:11.516 --> 54:13.618
the chimpanzee's lawyer?
(CHUCKLES)

54:15.853 --> 54:17.422
Mr. Frankenstein, I warn you

54:17.455 --> 54:20.725
that there are consequences
for obstructing police work.

54:20.758 --> 54:22.860
I should like to see records
of your experiments

54:22.894 --> 54:24.495
for the past twelve months.

54:24.529 --> 54:26.631
If you cannot cooperate,
then, by God,

54:26.664 --> 54:29.100
I'll conduct a thorough search
of these premises.

54:29.133 --> 54:30.535
"By God," you say?

54:34.138 --> 54:35.706
Inspector,
I must inform you...

54:35.740 --> 54:37.308
...that you are currently
in the home of rational,

54:37.341 --> 54:38.943
free-thinking men.

54:38.976 --> 54:40.578
To violate it or my research

54:40.611 --> 54:42.113
would require
a proper legal warrant.

54:42.146 --> 54:43.748
And God has no authority here.

54:43.781 --> 54:45.183
Tread lightly, sir.

54:46.150 --> 54:47.385
You may insult me,

54:47.418 --> 54:50.321
but you impugn the Lord
at your peril.

54:50.354 --> 54:52.723
I should remind you that life
is a sacred creation.

54:54.292 --> 54:56.928
Are you a police officer
or a theologian?

54:56.961 --> 54:58.162
Let me tell you something
for nothing.

54:58.196 --> 55:01.365
Life... I'll say this
very slowly... is merely...

55:01.399 --> 55:04.168
...the application and outcome
of applied chemistry.

55:04.202 --> 55:06.137
And did you or did you not
apply such chemistry

55:06.170 --> 55:07.939
at the Royal College
of Medicine two days ago?

55:07.972 --> 55:10.641
Igor, when was the last time
you went to confession?

55:10.675 --> 55:13.444
The good friar has come to see
whether we have sinned.

55:13.478 --> 55:15.079
"He that covereth his sin
shall not prosper."

55:15.112 --> 55:16.147
I'll ask you again.
(VICTOR SIGHS)

55:16.180 --> 55:17.915
And I will ask you again, sir:

55:17.949 --> 55:19.283
Why are you so interested,

55:19.317 --> 55:21.118
nay, infatuated
with this case?

55:21.152 --> 55:22.787
Surely there are
more interesting mysteries

55:22.820 --> 55:24.222
to be solved in London.

55:24.856 --> 55:26.424
Or...

55:26.457 --> 55:28.392
...is it precisely
because this experiment,

55:28.426 --> 55:30.828
which you imagine
took place...

55:30.862 --> 55:32.363
...may very well discredit

55:32.396 --> 55:34.165
your own primitive
belief system?

55:34.198 --> 55:36.400
Uncover what you will
about me, Inspector.

55:36.434 --> 55:38.336
Men like you have always stood
in the way of progress

55:38.369 --> 55:41.072
and invariably been
left in its wake.

55:41.105 --> 55:42.640
My creation...!

55:46.244 --> 55:47.378
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

55:51.215 --> 55:53.484
Be careful, Mr. Frankenstein.

55:54.252 --> 55:56.521
You toy with wrathful forces.

55:58.456 --> 56:00.625
And there's no mercy
in nature.

56:06.097 --> 56:07.365
Good day.

56:11.402 --> 56:12.937
I'll be back with a warrant.

56:32.056 --> 56:34.425
That thing
in the school, Igor...

56:36.661 --> 56:38.942
...I looked into its eyes
and there was nothing there.

56:43.868 --> 56:46.070
There is a difference
between using your machines...

56:46.103 --> 56:48.906
...to restore a life
wrongly lost and...

56:48.940 --> 56:51.442
...to create something that
was never supposed to exist.

56:52.543 --> 56:53.978
Victor must understand that.

56:54.512 --> 56:55.512
Look...

56:56.681 --> 56:59.617
...I never thought
I'd leave the circus.

56:59.650 --> 57:02.820
I thought I'd be in there
till I died. And Victor...

57:02.853 --> 57:05.289
...has given me all this.

57:06.557 --> 57:09.327
And all he asked
is that I believe in him.

57:09.360 --> 57:11.362
I understand that, Igor.

57:11.395 --> 57:13.664
What I'm saying is...

57:13.698 --> 57:16.334
...don't let yourself be
bullied by anyone ever again.

57:18.169 --> 57:19.704
Victor says he's your friend.

57:20.972 --> 57:23.040
But if you believe
Victor is on a wrong path,

57:23.074 --> 57:24.709
then you must make a stand.

57:31.782 --> 57:33.351
I have to go.

57:42.660 --> 57:46.664
Victor, if you truly respect
me as a scientist...

57:46.697 --> 57:48.766
If you truly respect me
as your friend...

57:49.634 --> 57:51.602
...you must listen
to my concerns.

57:56.574 --> 57:57.908
Igor.

57:57.942 --> 57:59.610
Sir.

57:59.644 --> 58:01.512
What's it been? Three years?

58:02.413 --> 58:03.781
You look slimmer.

58:04.915 --> 58:07.318
I'm sorry, sir, I don't...

58:07.351 --> 58:09.120
Is Victor here?
Yes, sir.

58:09.153 --> 58:10.488
Very well.

58:13.290 --> 58:15.092
Where have you been?

58:15.126 --> 58:17.762
Not wise to be out on the town
when there's a manhunt on.

58:18.496 --> 58:20.531
Get off his heart!

58:23.834 --> 58:24.834
Father.

58:25.603 --> 58:26.637
Get up.

58:29.073 --> 58:30.408
Leave.

58:34.111 --> 58:36.147
VICTOR: Father, I'm so excited
that you've come.

58:36.180 --> 58:37.415
Your timing is impeccable.

58:37.448 --> 58:38.349
I've had such
breakthroughs with my...

58:38.382 --> 58:39.684
I don't care.

58:41.085 --> 58:43.721
I don't care about your poorly
researched theories

58:43.754 --> 58:45.456
or your disastrous experiments.

58:45.489 --> 58:46.924
Not poorly researched,
I've told you...

58:46.957 --> 58:48.659
Victor, silence.

58:49.727 --> 58:51.862
Yesterday I received
a telegram...

58:51.896 --> 58:53.597
...informing me
that you are to go

58:53.631 --> 58:55.733
before the board of directors
at the college.

58:55.766 --> 58:57.902
They say you neglect
your schoolwork.

58:57.935 --> 58:59.403
(LAUGHING)

59:01.672 --> 59:03.574
They intend to expel you.

59:07.411 --> 59:09.447
No, they can't!

59:09.847 --> 59:11.115
Can't they?

59:11.148 --> 59:12.717
The work I am doing
is far more important...

59:12.750 --> 59:14.018
...than anything
they are conducting

59:14.051 --> 59:15.986
at that damn school.
You're a fool, Victor.

59:16.020 --> 59:17.822
You always have been.

59:19.490 --> 59:21.425
If only you could have been
more like Henry.

59:22.126 --> 59:23.561
But you...

59:25.129 --> 59:27.932
You just bring shame
to the name Frankenstein.

59:27.965 --> 59:29.500
I will ensure
that the name of Frankenstein

59:29.533 --> 59:30.601
is never forgotten!

59:30.968 --> 59:31.968
(GROANS)

59:35.139 --> 59:36.874
You've done it again, Victor.

59:38.676 --> 59:41.445
Only this time it's your own
life you've ruined.

59:48.519 --> 59:49.553
(DOOR CLOSES)

01:00:24.989 --> 01:00:26.757
So, what's this, then?

01:00:27.258 --> 01:00:29.059
Finnegan's project.

01:00:30.461 --> 01:00:31.662
My man.

01:00:33.764 --> 01:00:36.167
He was going to be
the modern Prometheus.

01:00:38.169 --> 01:00:40.771
Stupid, stupid, stupid.

01:00:44.341 --> 01:00:46.043
He's also not nearly
big enough.

01:00:46.610 --> 01:00:48.045
Yes. What?

01:00:49.313 --> 01:00:51.649
Gordon was fast
and strong, sure,

01:00:51.682 --> 01:00:52.983
but he couldn't sustain
any of that.

01:00:53.017 --> 01:00:54.051
And towards the end,

01:00:54.084 --> 01:00:55.920
he was having some
real trouble breathing.

01:00:55.953 --> 01:00:57.822
Breathing?

01:00:57.855 --> 01:01:00.691
Embolisms. Embolisms
in his lungs. Yes, of course.

01:01:01.525 --> 01:01:03.961
How stupid.

01:01:03.994 --> 01:01:06.363
So much raw energy
coursing around his structure.

01:01:06.397 --> 01:01:08.065
His body couldn't
take the charge.

01:01:08.098 --> 01:01:10.501
Wretched creature would have
been dead in ten minutes.

01:01:10.534 --> 01:01:13.270
If we want to build something
that can live and stay alive,

01:01:13.304 --> 01:01:14.605
we'll need a lot more energy.

01:01:14.638 --> 01:01:16.173
Tons more.

01:01:16.207 --> 01:01:18.576
Just stop. What could possibly
generate that kind of...?

01:01:19.643 --> 01:01:20.945
BOTH: Lightning!

01:01:23.514 --> 01:01:25.249
Yes, I have...

01:01:25.282 --> 01:01:26.684
...just the thing.

01:01:26.717 --> 01:01:29.119
One of my early designs
for the Lazarus Fork...

01:01:29.153 --> 01:01:30.454
...incorporated a structure

01:01:30.487 --> 01:01:33.324
that actually
sucked its energy...

01:01:33.357 --> 01:01:35.659
...from the atmosphere.

01:01:35.693 --> 01:01:37.761
It's possible that we can
build a larger version

01:01:37.795 --> 01:01:38.963
that would simulate
a static burst...

01:01:38.996 --> 01:01:41.599
...similar to
that of lightning.

01:01:41.632 --> 01:01:43.834
No, it's the same problem.

01:01:43.868 --> 01:01:46.871
We can't just make the body
accept that charge.

01:01:46.904 --> 01:01:49.807
We are incapable of simply
making larger organs.

01:01:49.840 --> 01:01:51.320
What if we gave him
two sets of lungs?

01:01:57.882 --> 01:01:59.402
You know you're brilliant,
don't you?

01:02:00.784 --> 01:02:03.821
Why wouldn't we? He's our man.
We can do what we like.

01:02:03.854 --> 01:02:06.090
Not just two sets of lungs...

01:02:06.123 --> 01:02:07.725
Two hearts.
Yes!

01:02:07.758 --> 01:02:09.493
Pump all that blood
around the larger body.

01:02:09.526 --> 01:02:11.046
Absolutely. He'd need it.
(LAUGHING)

01:02:13.397 --> 01:02:15.466
Igor...

01:02:15.499 --> 01:02:17.234
Earlier, when my father
was here...

01:02:17.268 --> 01:02:19.103
I was reading.

01:02:19.136 --> 01:02:20.404
I didn't hear a thing.

01:02:20.437 --> 01:02:21.757
Did he say
anything interesting?

01:02:26.210 --> 01:02:27.311
No, he didn't.

01:02:27.878 --> 01:02:28.878
Whiskey?

01:02:29.480 --> 01:02:31.315
Yes. Yes, do that.

01:02:40.558 --> 01:02:42.459
A larger chest cavity...

01:02:42.493 --> 01:02:44.828
...to incorporate four lungs.

01:02:44.862 --> 01:02:46.302
Two sets on the left
and the right.

01:02:49.366 --> 01:02:51.602
Bigger with the arms! Biceps.

01:02:52.803 --> 01:02:54.738
Now what do we do?
Tilt him.

01:02:54.772 --> 01:02:56.073
Backwards and forwards.

01:02:56.106 --> 01:02:57.775
Let that liquid
run through the body.

01:02:59.910 --> 01:03:01.478
Cheers.
Here's to him.

01:03:01.512 --> 01:03:02.813
Flat head.

01:03:04.281 --> 01:03:05.716
Why?

01:03:05.749 --> 01:03:08.085
Because I like it, that's why.

01:03:08.118 --> 01:03:09.653
(BOTH LAUGHING)

01:03:11.889 --> 01:03:13.490
To his two hearts.
(GLASSES CLINKING)

01:03:13.524 --> 01:03:15.059
(VICTOR CONTINUES LAUGHING)

01:03:25.336 --> 01:03:26.370
Mmm...

01:03:29.607 --> 01:03:30.975
(VICTOR SIGHS)

01:03:37.281 --> 01:03:38.649
Is that precious?

01:03:45.489 --> 01:03:47.569
ALISTAIR: They've denied us
the warrant, Inspector.

01:03:49.493 --> 01:03:51.228
As the Magistrate said,

01:03:51.261 --> 01:03:53.297
with no sign of any foul play,
nor indeed of any crime...

01:03:53.330 --> 01:03:54.698
No foul play?

01:03:55.699 --> 01:03:57.735
Look at the debris
at the Royal College.

01:03:57.768 --> 01:03:59.203
Acid burns, the same.

01:03:59.236 --> 01:04:00.738
Bloody paw prints
on the floor.

01:04:00.771 --> 01:04:02.139
Something's going on.

01:04:02.172 --> 01:04:04.212
Something's happening
in that basement, I know it.

01:04:04.274 --> 01:04:06.076
I know it.

01:04:06.110 --> 01:04:09.013
And it's my job, my duty.
It's my moral duty to stop it.

01:04:09.980 --> 01:04:12.516
But, sir, you have no warrant.

01:04:12.549 --> 01:04:14.084
Yes, he's insulted you.

01:04:14.118 --> 01:04:15.285
Yes, he's clever.
But we have no evidence.

01:04:15.719 --> 01:04:16.887
I don't care.

01:04:20.024 --> 01:04:21.864
I need to find out
what's in that basement.

01:04:23.093 --> 01:04:25.029
Now we can enact
my true vision.

01:04:25.062 --> 01:04:26.964
You and I will take
life's raw elements,

01:04:26.997 --> 01:04:30.234
its base components, and we...

01:04:30.267 --> 01:04:32.202
...shall assemble them
to our own specification,

01:04:32.236 --> 01:04:33.203
to our own design.

01:04:33.237 --> 01:04:34.805
(LAUGHING)

01:04:34.838 --> 01:04:37.474
For tonight we begin
our model...

01:04:38.142 --> 01:04:39.476
...of Prometheus.

01:04:41.311 --> 01:04:42.346
Um...

01:04:44.214 --> 01:04:47.751
Tonight... actually, Victor,
I was...

01:04:47.785 --> 01:04:48.652
I've been invited to a ball.

01:04:48.685 --> 01:04:50.287
A what?

01:04:50.320 --> 01:04:51.422
A ball. Lorelei's asked me.

01:04:51.455 --> 01:04:52.489
Lorelei?

01:04:53.524 --> 01:04:56.193
Yes.
No, no, don't speak.

01:04:57.094 --> 01:04:58.095
Lorelei...

01:04:59.930 --> 01:05:01.498
I shall stay here and work.

01:05:02.633 --> 01:05:04.368
I'm sorry, Victor.
No need to apologize.

01:05:06.003 --> 01:05:08.505
You should go off and enjoy
yourself. You deserve it.

01:05:09.173 --> 01:05:10.240
You've earned it.

01:05:11.408 --> 01:05:12.476
You can go now.

01:05:13.777 --> 01:05:14.845
Thank you.

01:05:21.452 --> 01:05:22.853
(OPERATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

01:05:32.296 --> 01:05:33.296
(ALL CHEER)

01:05:35.265 --> 01:05:37.968
(BOTH LAUGHING)

01:06:26.450 --> 01:06:28.051
I don't know what to do.

01:06:30.120 --> 01:06:31.922
You're already doing it.

01:06:56.146 --> 01:06:58.182
ALISTAIR: Frankenstein,
open this door!

01:06:59.416 --> 01:07:00.884
We'll break it down!

01:07:00.918 --> 01:07:03.353
Open this door now!
Scotland Yard!

01:07:07.057 --> 01:07:09.493
Frankenstein! Open the door!

01:07:14.231 --> 01:07:17.601
One, two, three.
One, two, three.

01:07:17.868 --> 01:07:19.336
Harder.

01:07:25.209 --> 01:07:28.078
Frankenstein! Open the door!

01:07:28.111 --> 01:07:29.213
(VICTOR GRUNTING)

01:07:30.681 --> 01:07:32.382
Victor, we have to leave!

01:07:32.416 --> 01:07:34.851
Where have you been?
With Lorelei.

01:07:34.885 --> 01:07:37.521
Oh, I see.
Wasting your time...

01:07:37.554 --> 01:07:39.690
...with pointless courtship...

01:07:39.723 --> 01:07:42.726
...while it remains to me to
take care of the work in hand!

01:07:42.759 --> 01:07:44.995
ALISTAIR: Frankenstein!
Open this door!

01:07:46.263 --> 01:07:49.766
Frankenstein, we're coming in!
Get this door down.

01:07:49.800 --> 01:07:50.834
I've sent for
one of Finnegan's men

01:07:50.867 --> 01:07:52.102
to provide a carriage.

01:07:52.135 --> 01:07:53.971
I'm trying to
overload the conductors.

01:07:54.004 --> 01:07:56.273
Forget the conductors!
We have to get out of here!

01:07:56.306 --> 01:07:59.376
And let them have my machines?
Not bloody likely!

01:08:01.245 --> 01:08:02.946
Trap door to the sewers...
it's the only way out.

01:08:02.980 --> 01:08:04.114
Try and open it.

01:08:10.087 --> 01:08:12.289
Pickaxe on the ice closet.

01:08:14.691 --> 01:08:16.193
(GASPS)

01:08:18.562 --> 01:08:20.397
What are you waiting for?
What is that?!

01:08:20.430 --> 01:08:22.165
Oh. Uh...

01:08:22.198 --> 01:08:24.167
Igor Straussman,
meet Igor Straussman.

01:08:25.269 --> 01:08:28.337
What? What did you do to him?!

01:08:28.372 --> 01:08:30.741
Found him like that
a couple months ago. Overdose.

01:08:30.774 --> 01:08:33.911
A couple of months?
You took his eyes!

01:08:33.944 --> 01:08:35.212
Victor, what is
wrong with you?

01:08:35.245 --> 01:08:36.813
You want to die in prison...

01:08:36.846 --> 01:08:38.814
...executed by that maniac?

01:08:38.849 --> 01:08:40.183
Hunchback!

01:08:42.586 --> 01:08:44.054
Do you see the truth now?

01:08:45.154 --> 01:08:47.925
This is the man
who took you from the circus.

01:08:47.957 --> 01:08:50.127
Who would gouge the eyes
from a dead friend.

01:08:50.160 --> 01:08:51.600
Move once more
and I'll kill you.

01:08:53.229 --> 01:08:56.066
Do as you wish.
I have no fear of death!

01:08:56.767 --> 01:08:57.767
TURPIN: Really?

01:08:59.303 --> 01:09:00.304
I do.

01:09:02.072 --> 01:09:03.473
I lost my wife...

01:09:05.542 --> 01:09:07.044
...to a malign growth.

01:09:08.444 --> 01:09:10.479
And in my suffering
I know about death.

01:09:11.615 --> 01:09:13.450
That it's an abyss from which

01:09:13.483 --> 01:09:16.319
no man nor woman
can be returned.

01:09:18.020 --> 01:09:20.490
Would you not rather
have her by your side?

01:09:20.524 --> 01:09:22.326
Would you not have her
live again?

01:09:23.926 --> 01:09:25.362
She is alive.

01:09:26.796 --> 01:09:28.064
In God's house.

01:09:28.999 --> 01:09:30.600
And when I, too,
fall into that abyss...

01:09:31.868 --> 01:09:33.337
...I shall be by her side.

01:09:34.404 --> 01:09:37.640
Don't you see?
You trust in a fiction!

01:09:38.642 --> 01:09:40.210
And you shall be forgotten.

01:09:41.645 --> 01:09:42.645
That's right.

01:09:43.880 --> 01:09:46.249
History will bury you,
Frankenstein...

01:09:46.283 --> 01:09:48.151
...and no man
will remember your name.

01:09:48.185 --> 01:09:49.752
No, you're wrong. Igor, no!

01:09:50.654 --> 01:09:51.654
(GRUNTING)

01:09:54.858 --> 01:09:56.360
You'll remember me now.

01:09:58.128 --> 01:09:59.229
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

01:10:00.864 --> 01:10:02.165
(VICTOR GROANS)

01:10:03.100 --> 01:10:04.301
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:10:11.608 --> 01:10:12.608
Victor!

01:10:13.677 --> 01:10:14.677
(SCREAMING)

01:10:20.784 --> 01:10:22.152
VICTOR: Come on, Igor!

01:10:23.286 --> 01:10:24.821
(CONTINUES SCREAMING)

01:10:25.889 --> 01:10:27.157
Pull! Pull!
(GRUNTING)

01:10:34.698 --> 01:10:36.800
Frankenstein, we're coming in!

01:10:38.468 --> 01:10:39.603
Inspector?

01:10:47.844 --> 01:10:49.312
Finnegan.

01:10:50.180 --> 01:10:52.549
Finnegan! Where are you?

01:10:52.582 --> 01:10:56.453
FINNEGAN: Frankenstein! Igor!
What an unexpected surprise.

01:10:56.486 --> 01:11:00.057
The police have raided my home
in search of Igor Straussman.

01:11:00.090 --> 01:11:02.225
We managed to avoid
incarceration, but...

01:11:02.259 --> 01:11:04.227
...it's just possible
we might have

01:11:04.261 --> 01:11:06.997
gravely wounded
a police officer.

01:11:07.030 --> 01:11:10.133
Ah. I suppose now you'll have
no choice but to leave London.

01:11:10.167 --> 01:11:12.102
Posthaste.
Very good.

01:11:12.135 --> 01:11:13.403
My family has an estate.

01:11:13.437 --> 01:11:15.705
The Castle Erskine
in Scotland. It's quite...

01:11:16.606 --> 01:11:18.041
...rural and secluded.

01:11:18.075 --> 01:11:19.843
Ideally situated,
you might say, for...

01:11:19.876 --> 01:11:21.845
...both your needs
as scientists and, um...

01:11:22.646 --> 01:11:23.713
...well, fugitives.

01:11:24.014 --> 01:11:25.315
Yes.

01:11:25.348 --> 01:11:27.184
I'll go and prepare the coach.

01:11:28.151 --> 01:11:29.719
Very good, thank you!

01:11:31.021 --> 01:11:33.223
How could you do that to me?
Do what?

01:11:33.256 --> 01:11:34.724
Keep from me
that you had killed a man

01:11:34.758 --> 01:11:36.093
and given me his name!

01:11:36.126 --> 01:11:37.627
I told you,
I did not kill Straussman.

01:11:37.661 --> 01:11:38.661
You're overreacting.

01:11:38.995 --> 01:11:40.363
You harvested his eyes!

01:11:40.397 --> 01:11:41.798
Details.

01:11:41.832 --> 01:11:43.099
He was a waste of space.

01:11:43.133 --> 01:11:45.168
This fanfare from you

01:11:45.202 --> 01:11:46.937
is more than his own family
will give him.

01:11:46.970 --> 01:11:48.472
All right, gentlemen,

01:11:48.505 --> 01:11:50.225
time is of the essence.
Your coach is ready.

01:11:50.707 --> 01:11:52.409
VICTOR: Come, Igor.

01:11:52.442 --> 01:11:53.410
We'll talk about this
on the way.

01:11:53.443 --> 01:11:54.478
No.

01:11:55.011 --> 01:11:56.446
What?

01:11:56.480 --> 01:11:58.148
What you're doing is wrong.
(LAUGHS)

01:11:59.316 --> 01:12:00.750
You've gone mad. Come.

01:12:00.784 --> 01:12:02.285
It's gone too far.

01:12:02.319 --> 01:12:04.287
We simply
do not have the time.

01:12:05.322 --> 01:12:06.556
I'm not leaving then.

01:12:08.258 --> 01:12:10.193
Listen to me.

01:12:10.227 --> 01:12:11.928
You have the chance here
to be part of...

01:12:11.962 --> 01:12:12.962
Of what?

01:12:13.530 --> 01:12:15.632
Of being lied to by you?

01:12:15.665 --> 01:12:18.602
Of being hunted by the police
and chased by monsters?

01:12:18.635 --> 01:12:19.970
Well, if you're going
to concentrate

01:12:20.003 --> 01:12:21.171
on the dark side.

01:12:21.204 --> 01:12:23.173
I'm not leaving.

01:12:23.206 --> 01:12:25.275
What will you do?
Go back to the circus?

01:12:25.308 --> 01:12:26.476
Resurrect your
illustrious career as...

01:12:26.510 --> 01:12:27.590
It's none of your concern.

01:12:33.817 --> 01:12:35.318
You're a fool.

01:12:39.656 --> 01:12:41.258
I created you.

01:12:42.726 --> 01:12:44.461
You think that just because
I put you in a back brace

01:12:44.494 --> 01:12:47.264
and you cut your hair...

01:12:47.297 --> 01:12:48.865
...you can
turn your back on me?

01:12:50.367 --> 01:12:52.736
That you can walk out
into the world on your own?

01:12:53.670 --> 01:12:56.072
See how far you get
with your acrobat

01:12:56.106 --> 01:12:57.674
and your morals
and your new life.

01:12:58.308 --> 01:12:59.876
Just come with me.

01:13:05.715 --> 01:13:06.715
Fine.

01:13:10.187 --> 01:13:11.621
I'm done with you.

01:13:28.939 --> 01:13:29.939
(COUGHS)

01:13:37.981 --> 01:13:40.517
You know... I knew
Igor Straussman.

01:13:42.586 --> 01:13:44.254
(SIGHS) He was a real bore.

01:13:44.988 --> 01:13:47.257
Nouveau riche. Drug addict.

01:13:48.425 --> 01:13:49.926
So, who are you then?

01:13:50.961 --> 01:13:51.961
Hmm?

01:13:52.495 --> 01:13:53.930
Doesn't matter really.

01:13:55.565 --> 01:13:58.201
Victor's been very forthcoming
with his designs.

01:13:58.234 --> 01:13:59.736
But I still need him for now.

01:14:02.272 --> 01:14:04.674
You, on the other hand...

01:14:06.343 --> 01:14:10.647
So, let's see. Your benefactor
has departed...

01:14:10.680 --> 01:14:13.550
...your home has been
ransacked by police...

01:14:15.218 --> 01:14:18.788
...your identity
revealed as a fraud...

01:14:18.822 --> 01:14:22.025
...and you know far too much
for me to let you walk away.

01:14:24.494 --> 01:14:26.062
What I'm getting at,
old boy...

01:14:27.797 --> 01:14:29.157
...is that
you won't be missed.

01:14:30.233 --> 01:14:31.301
(IGOR GRUNTING)

01:14:33.470 --> 01:14:35.070
Tie him up
and put him in the carriage.

01:14:36.973 --> 01:14:39.013
<i>You and Victor aren't
the only ones with vision.</i>

01:14:39.943 --> 01:14:42.345
I, too,
have a dream of the future.

01:14:42.379 --> 01:14:44.180
<i>A dream where my family</i>

01:14:44.214 --> 01:14:45.574
<i>will control
this new technology.</i>

01:14:46.216 --> 01:14:47.717
Hmm? What's that?

01:14:49.119 --> 01:14:50.787
<i>You don't approve.</i>

01:14:50.820 --> 01:14:53.590
No, I imagined you and Victor
wouldn't like that much.

01:14:54.624 --> 01:14:57.460
You know, for men
obsessed with death,

01:14:57.494 --> 01:14:59.174
you think yourselves
so above violence.

01:15:01.598 --> 01:15:02.732
Curious.

01:15:04.267 --> 01:15:05.669
<i>Good-bye, Igor.</i>

01:15:18.181 --> 01:15:20.016
(MUFFLED GRUNTING)

01:15:58.188 --> 01:15:59.856
Straussman wasn't Straussman.

01:16:01.157 --> 01:16:03.893
The body, the frozen creature,
that was Straussman.

01:16:03.927 --> 01:16:05.228
The young man pretending
to be Straussman

01:16:05.261 --> 01:16:06.329
was the hunchback...

01:16:06.362 --> 01:16:07.530
...transformed
by Frankenstein.

01:16:07.564 --> 01:16:08.765
Inspector, this is not...

01:16:08.798 --> 01:16:10.967
They escaped in the
Finnegan family coach.

01:16:11.000 --> 01:16:12.469
Finnegan attends
the Royal College of Medicine.

01:16:12.502 --> 01:16:14.170
It makes sense.

01:16:14.204 --> 01:16:16.172
He's in on it, too,
maybe funding them.

01:16:16.206 --> 01:16:17.240
CHIEF INSPECTOR:
Inspector Turpin, stop...

01:16:17.273 --> 01:16:18.742
TURPIN: My guess is that
he's fled the country by now,

01:16:18.775 --> 01:16:21.277
more than likely
alongside Finnegan...

01:16:21.311 --> 01:16:22.345
...who, a little digging
shows, has an estate,

01:16:22.379 --> 01:16:24.514
Castle Erskine in Scotland.

01:16:24.547 --> 01:16:25.982
We'll find them there.

01:16:26.015 --> 01:16:27.350
Stop it, Roderick, damn it!

01:16:27.384 --> 01:16:28.985
No, listen to me!

01:16:29.018 --> 01:16:30.787
We can catch them now.

01:16:31.888 --> 01:16:33.022
We can...

01:16:33.923 --> 01:16:34.923
...and we will.

01:16:39.596 --> 01:16:41.831
What do you mean?

01:16:41.865 --> 01:16:44.434
You're being removed
from the case... sir.

01:16:45.268 --> 01:16:47.537
From the whole force, in fact.

01:16:47.570 --> 01:16:49.773
Constable Alistair will be
taking your place.

01:16:49.806 --> 01:16:52.509
You are on a medical
and mental reprieve.

01:16:54.444 --> 01:16:56.579
You had no warrant, Roderick.

01:16:57.981 --> 01:17:00.183
Do you have any idea
the lengths I have been to...

01:17:00.216 --> 01:17:02.652
...in order to protect you
from criminal charges?

01:17:03.620 --> 01:17:05.722
It was a necessary action. Really?

01:17:07.390 --> 01:17:08.925
In pursuit of what?

01:17:10.693 --> 01:17:12.729
High society hunchbacks?

01:17:13.563 --> 01:17:15.932
Undead monsters?

01:17:17.233 --> 01:17:18.635
Conspiracies involving

01:17:18.668 --> 01:17:20.437
one of the richest families
in England?

01:17:20.470 --> 01:17:22.806
Yes, a conspiracy
to create life in...

01:17:25.008 --> 01:17:28.077
...a direct, defiant action
against God.

01:17:29.846 --> 01:17:32.448
You were the best detective
Scotland Yard had,

01:17:32.482 --> 01:17:33.950
but now it's time
for you to rest.

01:17:33.983 --> 01:17:35.952
You must heal.
And when you return,

01:17:35.985 --> 01:17:38.221
you will see things
how they really are.

01:17:46.362 --> 01:17:47.530
(IGOR COUGHING)

01:18:26.536 --> 01:18:27.670
IGOR: <i>Is that precious?</i>

01:18:30.473 --> 01:18:32.942
I took possession of this
when I was... ten.

01:18:34.544 --> 01:18:36.913
It was a very cold winter
that year.

01:18:36.946 --> 01:18:39.048
We lived in the country then.
It was a happy time.

01:18:39.949 --> 01:18:41.784
We crept out of
my bedroom window

01:18:41.818 --> 01:18:42.652
because we wanted to
play in the snow...

01:18:42.685 --> 01:18:43.887
...and so we did.

01:18:45.088 --> 01:18:46.289
Until we were...

01:18:47.557 --> 01:18:49.158
...engulfed by a blizzard.

01:18:51.394 --> 01:18:52.962
I almost died.

01:18:54.631 --> 01:18:56.399
Anyway, when...

01:18:56.432 --> 01:18:57.767
When the snow cleared...

01:18:58.868 --> 01:19:00.703
...and dawn finally broke...

01:19:02.505 --> 01:19:03.907
...I was alive.

01:19:07.577 --> 01:19:09.712
I looked into my hand
and I was holding this.

01:19:11.581 --> 01:19:13.116
It serves to remind me.

01:19:15.518 --> 01:19:17.053
Remind you of what?

01:19:18.688 --> 01:19:19.989
That God...

01:19:23.226 --> 01:19:24.928
...if at all He does exist...

01:19:27.130 --> 01:19:29.933
...sent us
into this world imperfect.

01:19:32.368 --> 01:19:33.803
We're weak.

01:19:34.504 --> 01:19:35.939
We're fragile.

01:19:37.807 --> 01:19:39.342
And we're destined to die.

01:19:43.880 --> 01:19:46.015
This reminds me that
that is not good enough.

01:19:47.483 --> 01:19:48.885
Who were you with?

01:19:49.585 --> 01:19:50.620
VICTOR: Hmm?

01:19:51.888 --> 01:19:53.957
You said "we".
In the blizzard.

01:19:54.290 --> 01:19:55.290
Did I?

01:20:14.510 --> 01:20:17.180
Where in God's name
do you think you're going?

01:20:17.213 --> 01:20:18.653
You haven't been
out of bed in weeks!

01:20:18.681 --> 01:20:20.049
You can barely walk!

01:20:21.117 --> 01:20:23.853
Igor. Igor, don't go.
Don't do this.

01:20:23.886 --> 01:20:25.822
I have to go. He needs me.

01:20:27.156 --> 01:20:28.324
You owe him nothing.

01:20:29.325 --> 01:20:30.093
You're your own man.

01:20:30.326 --> 01:20:31.326
No.

01:20:31.894 --> 01:20:33.396
I'm the man he made me.

01:20:34.630 --> 01:20:35.932
You're wrong.

01:20:37.033 --> 01:20:39.168
You've always been
this person.

01:20:39.202 --> 01:20:41.337
This brave,
brilliant, beautiful person.

01:20:41.804 --> 01:20:43.873
He gave me a life.

01:20:46.342 --> 01:20:48.144
I'm sorry, Lorelei, but...

01:20:48.978 --> 01:20:51.214
...you must understand,
I have to go.

01:20:52.515 --> 01:20:54.017
He's my friend.

01:20:56.719 --> 01:20:58.421
Then you will not go alone.

01:21:10.767 --> 01:21:12.602
VICTOR: <i>Two hearts.</i>

01:21:12.635 --> 01:21:14.437
<i>Pump all that blood
around the larger body.</i>

01:21:18.975 --> 01:21:22.712
<i>A larger chest cavity
to incorporate four lungs.</i>

01:21:22.745 --> 01:21:24.781
<i>Two sets on the left
and the right.</i>

01:21:38.161 --> 01:21:40.563
<i>You and I, Igor...
we shall create a man...</i>

01:21:40.596 --> 01:21:42.999
<i>...after our own image.</i>

01:21:49.739 --> 01:21:51.140
<i>An intelligent...</i>

01:21:51.607 --> 01:21:53.276
<i>...civilized...</i>

01:21:53.676 --> 01:21:55.344
<i>...man.</i>

01:21:55.378 --> 01:21:56.379
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:22:14.664 --> 01:22:15.765
IGOR: Stop!

01:22:17.733 --> 01:22:19.268
Stop here!
DRIVER: Whoa!

01:22:24.874 --> 01:22:26.109
IGOR: Finnegan's men.

01:22:27.543 --> 01:22:28.543
Wait here.

01:22:32.749 --> 01:22:34.117
Please take care.

01:22:38.187 --> 01:22:40.123
What are you doing?
Go.

01:22:55.238 --> 01:22:56.272
Hello?

01:22:57.473 --> 01:22:59.208
Sorry, we seem to be lost.

01:23:06.582 --> 01:23:07.884
Thank you!

01:23:08.518 --> 01:23:10.119
(IGOR PANTING)

01:23:14.924 --> 01:23:16.359
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:23:20.196 --> 01:23:21.230
What's this?

01:23:42.618 --> 01:23:44.554
Hold her here.
I'm going to the castle.

01:23:44.587 --> 01:23:47.056
Sir, there is a storm coming.

01:23:47.089 --> 01:23:50.593
That man is in allegiance with
Satan... and must be stopped!

01:24:09.412 --> 01:24:11.347
DETTWEILER:
All stations ready!

01:24:11.380 --> 01:24:14.750
VICTOR: Engineers! Scientists!
Eyes to me!

01:24:14.784 --> 01:24:17.053
The storm is nigh!

01:24:17.086 --> 01:24:21.891
The storm is nigh!
Conditions are perfect!

01:24:25.895 --> 01:24:29.031
ENGINEER: Electrical station
ready, sir!

01:24:29.065 --> 01:24:30.366
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:24:33.436 --> 01:24:36.239
Prometheus moving,
station one!

01:24:36.272 --> 01:24:38.307
(MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

01:24:43.346 --> 01:24:46.282
ENGINEER 2: Stoke the furnace!
We need it hotter!

01:24:46.315 --> 01:24:47.635
ENGINEER 3:
Mind the blood pipe!

01:24:53.623 --> 01:24:55.258
Prepare the blood!

01:24:55.291 --> 01:24:57.193
ENGINEER 1: Fluid station now!

01:24:58.694 --> 01:25:00.196
VICTOR: Now. Set?

01:25:01.764 --> 01:25:03.266
Inserting.

01:25:03.299 --> 01:25:05.101
In. Tapped.

01:25:05.134 --> 01:25:06.502
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

01:25:13.843 --> 01:25:16.946
Respiratory station!

01:25:16.979 --> 01:25:19.081
DETTWEILER: Prepare
the respiratory station!

01:25:20.616 --> 01:25:21.617
Victor.

01:25:22.852 --> 01:25:24.654
Igor?

01:25:24.687 --> 01:25:26.522
I'm so glad you've come.

01:25:26.555 --> 01:25:28.958
Victor, Finnegan tried to
have me killed.

01:25:28.991 --> 01:25:30.926
I believe he intends to
kill you, too,

01:25:30.960 --> 01:25:33.195
when you've given him
what he wants.

01:25:33.229 --> 01:25:35.197
We can still get out of this,

01:25:35.231 --> 01:25:36.699
but you must stop
this experiment.

01:25:36.732 --> 01:25:38.000
Father sent you, didn't he?

01:25:38.034 --> 01:25:39.502
Don't be ridiculous!

01:25:39.535 --> 01:25:40.870
He'll stop at nothing,

01:25:40.903 --> 01:25:42.543
and you don't know
what he's capable of!

01:25:43.773 --> 01:25:44.874
I don't care.

01:25:44.907 --> 01:25:46.442
What?

01:25:46.475 --> 01:25:48.678
Finnegan's motives
mean nothing to me.

01:25:48.711 --> 01:25:52.181
I will turn the tide of human
existence here, tonight.

01:25:52.214 --> 01:25:55.284
Then this world
which has spurned me...

01:25:55.318 --> 01:25:57.920
...will forever
remember my name!

01:25:57.954 --> 01:25:59.422
No, if you do what he asks,

01:25:59.455 --> 01:26:01.357
no one will remember
Frankenstein the man.

01:26:01.390 --> 01:26:02.658
Only the monster!
(GRUNTING)

01:26:03.726 --> 01:26:04.727
(GROANING)

01:26:06.028 --> 01:26:08.497
I forgive you, Igor.

01:26:08.531 --> 01:26:10.700
I forgive you this remarkable
lack of foresight.

01:26:10.733 --> 01:26:12.101
So stay here!

01:26:12.969 --> 01:26:14.503
Your brother was with you!

01:26:16.005 --> 01:26:17.907
Henry Frankenstein.

01:26:17.940 --> 01:26:19.408
He was with you that night.

01:26:20.977 --> 01:26:22.545
Was he older
or younger than you?

01:26:23.379 --> 01:26:25.114
He was older.

01:26:25.147 --> 01:26:26.749
You must have
looked up to him.

01:26:30.219 --> 01:26:32.088
Where did you get that?

01:26:32.121 --> 01:26:33.456
I wouldn't be surprised

01:26:33.489 --> 01:26:35.791
if it was your idea, though.
Was it?

01:26:35.825 --> 01:26:38.227
To go out into the snow.
And he protected you.

01:26:39.228 --> 01:26:41.297
And he died while you lived.

01:26:44.066 --> 01:26:46.235
Isn't that what
all this is about, Victor?

01:26:47.136 --> 01:26:49.372
You want to stop
other people...

01:26:49.405 --> 01:26:51.574
...from having to endure
that pain that you felt.

01:26:56.312 --> 01:26:57.312
No.

01:26:57.546 --> 01:26:58.546
No?

01:27:00.850 --> 01:27:02.118
No.

01:27:06.222 --> 01:27:08.391
It's about so much
more than that.

01:27:11.027 --> 01:27:14.196
Don't you see? To my mind...

01:27:14.230 --> 01:27:15.731
I took my brother's life
that night.

01:27:20.102 --> 01:27:22.538
I have to redress the balance.

01:27:25.141 --> 01:27:28.210
I have to create life now.

01:27:29.678 --> 01:27:33.816
Victor, none of this
does that.

01:27:33.849 --> 01:27:38.254
This only brings
more and more and more pain.

01:27:40.356 --> 01:27:42.558
And whatever path this is
that you've gone down,

01:27:42.591 --> 01:27:44.160
this is not you.

01:27:44.960 --> 01:27:47.229
You're a good man, Victor.

01:27:58.240 --> 01:28:00.443
Igor...
FINNEGAN: Frankenstein!

01:28:00.476 --> 01:28:03.446
Frankenstein! Hurry, man!
The storm is almost upon us!

01:28:06.515 --> 01:28:07.516
Victor...

01:28:07.950 --> 01:28:09.251
...don't.

01:28:13.489 --> 01:28:14.657
Victor!

01:28:20.129 --> 01:28:22.565
ENGINEER 1: Station one ready!

01:28:22.598 --> 01:28:24.518
(MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:28:31.574 --> 01:28:33.175
Prometheus moving!

01:28:35.778 --> 01:28:38.214
Electrical station!

01:28:38.247 --> 01:28:40.549
ENGINEER 2: Electrical station
ready, sir!

01:28:54.363 --> 01:28:56.265
FINNEGAN:
Who'd have thought it, eh?

01:28:56.298 --> 01:28:59.468
You and I on the threshold
of immortality.

01:29:04.707 --> 01:29:06.809
Prometheus moving!

01:29:07.209 --> 01:29:08.777
Lazarus station!

01:29:09.311 --> 01:29:10.813
Damn them all, eh?

01:29:11.780 --> 01:29:14.817
The naysayers... and
the hypocrites.

01:29:20.422 --> 01:29:22.658
For tonight, Victor,
we breathe life...

01:29:23.092 --> 01:29:24.660
...into flesh!

01:29:30.132 --> 01:29:32.234
ENGINEER 1: Balloons released!

01:29:51.053 --> 01:29:52.454
Lazarus Fork.

01:29:53.689 --> 01:29:54.689
(EXHALES)

01:30:00.462 --> 01:30:02.932
I will give you life.

01:30:03.666 --> 01:30:05.267
I will give you...

01:30:05.701 --> 01:30:06.701
...life!

01:30:10.873 --> 01:30:14.009
Prometheus ascending!

01:30:27.156 --> 01:30:28.557
ENGINEER 1:
Station ready, sir!

01:30:29.558 --> 01:30:31.594
VICTOR: I want full power,
on my mark.

01:30:31.627 --> 01:30:32.627
Now!

01:30:33.529 --> 01:30:36.298
Converter B standing by.

01:30:36.332 --> 01:30:37.700
Full power... now!

01:30:41.203 --> 01:30:43.038
All positions, relays open!

01:30:49.411 --> 01:30:50.980
This is your moment, Victor!

01:30:51.647 --> 01:30:52.647
Victor!

01:30:53.182 --> 01:30:54.650
It's too much power!

01:30:57.653 --> 01:30:59.054
IGOR: <i>You know this story.</i>

01:31:01.991 --> 01:31:03.325
<i>The crack of lightning.</i>

01:31:04.994 --> 01:31:06.729
<i>A mad genius.</i>

01:31:09.565 --> 01:31:11.300
<i>An unholy creation.</i>

01:31:12.368 --> 01:31:13.402
IGOR: Victor...

01:31:15.404 --> 01:31:16.438
...don't!

01:31:18.207 --> 01:31:21.076
Live!

01:32:05.187 --> 01:32:06.388
Well, Victor.

01:32:10.959 --> 01:32:12.361
Sir, I must warn you...

01:32:15.197 --> 01:32:16.865
...we are overloading!

01:32:28.844 --> 01:32:30.379
(MEN SCREAMING)

01:32:33.082 --> 01:32:34.817
(VICTOR YELLING)
(SCREAMING)

01:32:35.684 --> 01:32:36.785
No!
(FINNEGAN SCREAMING)

01:32:38.120 --> 01:32:39.455
(SCREAMING)

01:32:47.196 --> 01:32:48.764
No!

01:32:50.399 --> 01:32:52.034
(MEN SCREAMING)
(VICTOR GROANING)

01:33:17.292 --> 01:33:18.427
(YELPS)

01:33:38.914 --> 01:33:40.482
Frankenstein!

01:33:43.419 --> 01:33:46.255
You will burn
for what you do here.

01:33:46.288 --> 01:33:48.390
This isn't science.

01:33:48.424 --> 01:33:49.824
This is the work
of Satan himself.

01:33:50.325 --> 01:33:51.760
(LAUGHING)

01:33:54.463 --> 01:33:58.901
There's no Satan.
No God. Only humanity.

01:33:59.301 --> 01:34:00.869
Only me!

01:34:05.307 --> 01:34:06.675
(CHAINS RATTLING)

01:34:32.601 --> 01:34:34.069
May God forgive you,
Frankenstein!

01:34:34.102 --> 01:34:35.971
May God forgive you!

01:35:02.264 --> 01:35:03.765
Out of the way, Victor!

01:35:04.233 --> 01:35:05.634
Out of the way!

01:35:06.168 --> 01:35:07.603
Come to me.

01:35:13.075 --> 01:35:14.610
I am your brother.

01:35:59.855 --> 01:36:01.957
Oh, my brother Henry,
forgive me.

01:36:05.594 --> 01:36:07.229
I have wronged you.

01:36:09.197 --> 01:36:11.099
For this is not life.

01:36:13.335 --> 01:36:15.938
(SOBBING) This is not life!

01:36:18.040 --> 01:36:20.208
You are not life!

01:36:20.575 --> 01:36:22.110
Live!

01:36:22.144 --> 01:36:24.279
Victor!
Out of the way, Frankenstein!

01:36:24.313 --> 01:36:26.214
Live! Live! Live!

01:36:26.915 --> 01:36:28.684
(GROWLS)

01:36:33.121 --> 01:36:34.121
(CHOKING)

01:36:45.200 --> 01:36:47.502
May God drive out
this devil...

01:36:47.536 --> 01:36:49.204
...and be driven back
to the pits of hell

01:36:49.237 --> 01:36:50.237
from whence he came.

01:36:51.173 --> 01:36:52.173
(GUN CLICKS)

01:36:54.242 --> 01:36:55.410
No!

01:37:15.697 --> 01:37:17.065
(PANTING)

01:37:33.281 --> 01:37:36.284
Igor, I'm sorry.
What are we going to do?

01:37:36.318 --> 01:37:37.819
What are we going to do now?

01:37:41.857 --> 01:37:44.459
We will do the only thing
we can do.

01:37:45.594 --> 01:37:47.295
(OBJECTS CRASHING)
(GLASS SHATTERING)

01:37:55.670 --> 01:37:56.772
Huh?

01:38:09.451 --> 01:38:10.452
Shit.

01:38:21.396 --> 01:38:22.476
(VICTOR YELLING)
(GROANING)

01:38:30.205 --> 01:38:31.239
No!

01:39:08.643 --> 01:39:09.643
Igor!

01:39:14.316 --> 01:39:15.450
(YELLING)

01:39:19.121 --> 01:39:20.388
(ROARS)

01:39:24.793 --> 01:39:26.261
Victor...
(GROANS)

01:39:27.162 --> 01:39:28.163
...get off.

01:39:31.600 --> 01:39:32.600
(SCREAMING)

01:39:43.345 --> 01:39:44.345
(PANTING)

01:39:55.724 --> 01:39:56.724
(GROANING)

01:40:00.795 --> 01:40:02.898
(HEART BEATING)

01:40:05.267 --> 01:40:06.568
Igor!

01:40:08.003 --> 01:40:09.337
Two hearts!
(ROARS)

01:40:11.173 --> 01:40:12.474
No!

01:40:25.787 --> 01:40:26.787
(GROANING)

01:40:43.638 --> 01:40:46.141
Oh, my brother, forgive me!

01:40:46.174 --> 01:40:47.694
(VICTOR GRUNTING)
(MONSTER GROANING)

01:41:54.910 --> 01:41:56.144
Victor?

01:42:43.258 --> 01:42:45.026
VICTOR: <i>Dearest Igor:</i>

01:42:45.060 --> 01:42:47.062
<i>I would have
waited for you, but...</i>

01:42:47.095 --> 01:42:48.897
<i>...three's a crowd
and all that.</i>

01:42:48.930 --> 01:42:50.398
<i>Besides, I think</i>

01:42:50.432 --> 01:42:52.072
<i>you've probably had enough
of my work.</i>

01:42:52.100 --> 01:42:53.980
<i>Truth be told, you've probably
had enough of me.</i>

01:42:55.170 --> 01:42:56.438
<i>Our time together is done.</i>

01:42:56.471 --> 01:42:58.139
<i>Our achievements
are in the past...</i>

01:42:58.173 --> 01:43:01.176
<i>...and our discoveries
will probably never be known.</i>

01:43:01.209 --> 01:43:02.977
<i>But I will always
think of you fondly,</i>

01:43:03.011 --> 01:43:05.313
<i>and always as my friend.</i>

01:43:05.914 --> 01:43:07.682
<i>As for myself...</i>

01:43:07.716 --> 01:43:09.217
<i>...I have some ideas</i>

01:43:09.250 --> 01:43:11.052
<i>about where we went wrong
this time...</i>

01:43:11.086 --> 01:43:13.355
<i>...and one day I may
call on you once more.</i>

01:43:13.788 --> 01:43:15.457
<i>Be ready.</i>

01:43:15.490 --> 01:43:18.593
<i>For now,
your life is your own...</i>

01:43:18.626 --> 01:43:20.495
<i>...and I wish you
luck with it.</i>

01:43:22.230 --> 01:43:25.633
<i>You are and will remain
my greatest creation.</i>

01:43:27.435 --> 01:43:28.503
<i>Your friend...</i>

01:43:29.305 --> 01:43:35.825
